The topics we will consider

00:00:14.220 --> 00:00:16.790
today are the world economy, international

00:00:16.800 --> 00:00:18.010
economic relations, balance

00:00:18.020 --> 00:00:19.750
in the international

00:00:19.760 --> 00:00:21.070
economy, modern development

00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:23.230
of international economic

00:00:23.240 --> 00:00:24.650
relations, state

00:00:25.390 --> 00:00:26.490
regulation of foreign

00:00:26.500 --> 00:00:27.550
trade.

00:00:28.210 --> 00:00:29.690
The final theme of our discussion

00:00:29.700 --> 00:00:31.250
will be the international financial

00:00:31.260 --> 00:00:34.010
system and currency regulation.

00:00:34.270 --> 00:00:36.270
The first question I would like to

00:00:36.280 --> 00:00:38.770
address is the position of the

00:00:38.780 --> 00:00:41.210
subject of international economic

00:00:41.220 --> 00:00:42.950
relations in the system of scientific

00:00:42.960 --> 00:00:43.850
knowledge.

00:00:43.930 --> 00:00:45.990
There are currently two

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:48.670
positions, two approaches

00:00:48.680 --> 00:00:51.890
to this issue.

00:00:52.190 --> 00:00:53.830
One group of authors believes that

00:00:53.840 --> 00:00:54.970
international economic relations

00:00:54.980 --> 00:00:56.850
are fully included in the course

00:00:56.860 --> 00:00:58.390
of international economy.

00:00:59.050 --> 00:01:00.890
Another group of authors believes that

00:01:00.900 --> 00:01:03.310
this is an independent course that

00:01:03.320 --> 00:01:05.270
considers more specific economic

00:01:05.280 --> 00:01:06.990
relationships.

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:09.530
Please look at the scheme.

00:01:10.590 --> 00:01:12.030
In principle, micro- and

00:01:12.040 --> 00:01:13.470
macroeconomics, as general

00:01:13.480 --> 00:01:15.570
theoretical sciences, are the

00:01:15.580 --> 00:01:18.330
basis of all scientific knowledge

00:01:18.340 --> 00:01:19.710
related to international

00:01:19.720 --> 00:01:21.470
economic relations.

00:01:21.670 --> 00:01:23.430
International economics,

00:01:23.440 --> 00:01:25.710
as a subject, is part of economic

00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:29.410
theory and includes both

00:01:29.420 --> 00:01:31.490
international economic relations

00:01:31.500 --> 00:01:33.550
and the characteristics

00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:35.550
of the world economy.

00:01:35.850 --> 00:01:38.270
In the process of developing scientific

00:01:38.280 --> 00:01:40.150
knowledge, international

00:01:40.160 --> 00:01:41.510
economic relations as

00:01:41.590 --> 00:01:43.490
a subject have become more

00:01:43.500 --> 00:01:45.450
independent and have become

00:01:45.460 --> 00:01:47.070
more independent.

00:01:48.530 --> 00:01:52.670
This course deals with more

00:01:52.680 --> 00:01:55.650
specific economic relations.

00:01:56.270 --> 00:01:58.230
And the international economy

00:01:58.240 --> 00:01:59.950
is closely related to the following

00:01:59.960 --> 00:02:01.310
course of foreign

00:02:01.320 --> 00:02:03.490
economic activity of the FIR.

00:02:04.450 --> 00:02:06.810
On the other hand, such a course as

00:02:06.820 --> 00:02:10.390
world economy considers the problems

00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:14.010
of different regions and is quite

00:02:14.020 --> 00:02:16.530
closely related to the

00:02:16.540 --> 00:02:18.810
subject of economic geography.

00:02:19.070 --> 00:02:23.770
The object of the world economy

00:02:23.780 --> 00:02:25.930
is the world economy as a whole.

00:02:26.590 --> 00:02:28.430
But as for the subject, we will pay

00:02:28.440 --> 00:02:30.230
attention first of all to the development

00:02:30.240 --> 00:02:31.410
of international economic

00:02:31.420 --> 00:02:33.290
relations and their

00:02:33.300 --> 00:02:35.670
modern forms.

00:02:36.090 --> 00:02:37.230
The subject of international

00:02:37.240 --> 00:02:39.510
economic relations are firms, individuals,

00:02:39.520 --> 00:02:43.270
non-profit organizations,

00:02:43.280 --> 00:02:45.610
national economies in the

00:02:46.090 --> 00:02:47.730
person of the state, regional

00:02:47.740 --> 00:02:51.450
systems in the person of regional-

00:02:51.460 --> 00:02:53.410
state institutions and even

00:02:53.420 --> 00:02:55.590
international economic

00:02:55.600 --> 00:02:57.450
organizations.

00:02:57.690 --> 00:02:59.330
The new subjects, of course,

00:02:59.630 --> 00:03:00.570
are non-profit organizations

00:03:00.580 --> 00:03:02.770
and international economic

00:03:02.780 --> 00:03:06.210
organizations, which have been

00:03:06.220 --> 00:03:07.890
actively involved in the process

00:03:07.900 --> 00:03:10.270
of regulating international

00:03:10.280 --> 00:03:12.270
economic relations.

00:03:12.470 --> 00:03:14.950
The world economy can be

00:03:14.960 --> 00:03:17.890
defined as a set of national

00:03:17.900 --> 00:03:19.370
economies.

00:03:19.590 --> 00:03:21.650
It is a combination, because

00:03:21.660 --> 00:03:23.190
it is assumed that there are

00:03:23.200 --> 00:03:27.170
quite close relationships between them.

00:03:27.310 --> 00:03:31.170
And such a set of countries has a greater

00:03:31.180 --> 00:03:33.670
impact on the development of the world

00:03:33.680 --> 00:03:35.470
economy as a whole than the simple

00:03:35.480 --> 00:03:36.670
sum of countries.

00:03:37.450 --> 00:03:39.490
The development of the world economy

00:03:39.500 --> 00:03:42.010
is linked to a number of major factors.

00:03:42.570 --> 00:03:45.250
First of all, the first such

00:03:45.260 --> 00:03:46.750
factor affecting the development

00:03:46.760 --> 00:03:48.610
of the world economy is the uneven

00:03:48.620 --> 00:03:50.410
distribution of production

00:03:50.420 --> 00:03:51.810
factors on the territory

00:03:51.820 --> 00:03:52.870
of the land.

00:03:53.230 --> 00:03:55.530
This was once addressed by Adam Smith,

00:03:55.540 --> 00:03:58.130
and then by David Ricardo.

00:03:58.430 --> 00:04:00.410
They proved that the cause of

00:04:00.420 --> 00:04:03.630
international exchange is the difference

00:04:03.640 --> 00:04:07.030
in labor productivity in individual

00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:08.190
countries.

00:04:08.210 --> 00:04:09.170
In turn, this productivity

00:04:09.180 --> 00:04:10.950
of labour is based on the

00:04:10.960 --> 00:04:13.590
fact that countries have

00:04:13.600 --> 00:04:16.410
different factors of production.

00:04:17.290 --> 00:04:19.050
The next factor that influences the

00:04:19.060 --> 00:04:20.950
development of the world economy is

00:04:20.960 --> 00:04:22.630
the movement of production factors.

00:04:22.650 --> 00:04:24.550
In economic theory, it is called

00:04:24.560 --> 00:04:26.610
the term of the mobility of

00:04:26.620 --> 00:04:27.990
production factors.

00:04:29.790 --> 00:04:32.050
All these processes – the movement of

00:04:32.060 --> 00:04:33.770
factors of production, the presence

00:04:33.780 --> 00:04:35.250
of factors of production in some countries

00:04:35.260 --> 00:04:37.050
– contribute to the development

00:04:44.040 --> 00:04:46.550
of international division of labour

00:04:46.560 --> 00:04:48.210
and the international division of

00:04:48.220 --> 00:04:50.730
factors of production.

00:04:50.970 --> 00:04:51.870
First of all, in the

00:04:51.880 --> 00:04:54.310
course of economic theory, you once

00:04:54.320 --> 00:04:55.690
understood such factors

00:04:55.700 --> 00:04:57.270
of production as labor, land,

00:04:57.350 --> 00:04:59.690
capital, entrepreneurial capacity.

00:05:00.570 --> 00:05:01.790
In the present day,

00:05:01.800 --> 00:05:06.750
these factors are developing.

00:05:07.730 --> 00:05:09.030
And, in principle, if you start

00:05:09.040 --> 00:05:10.210
listing those factors

00:05:10.220 --> 00:05:15.550
of production, which are associated

00:05:15.830 --> 00:05:18.750
with a sufficiently large list.

00:05:18.930 --> 00:05:20.870
Based on this, modern statistics, in

00:05:20.880 --> 00:05:23.810
particular the International

00:05:23.820 --> 00:05:25.330
Statistical Commission of the United

00:05:25.340 --> 00:05:27.330
Nations, has proposed to divide the

00:05:27.340 --> 00:05:29.370
factors into primary and secondary.

00:05:29.730 --> 00:05:31.370
Of course, the primary factors

00:05:31.380 --> 00:05:32.970
will remain labor, land,

00:05:33.030 --> 00:05:35.210
capital and entrepreneurial capacity.

00:05:35.690 --> 00:05:38.190
But the secondary factors that

00:05:38.200 --> 00:05:39.950
are developing right now are

00:05:39.960 --> 00:05:42.510
information, technology and

00:05:42.520 --> 00:05:46.030
even government regulation.

00:05:46.350 --> 00:05:48.930
I draw your attention to the fact

00:05:48.940 --> 00:05:50.390
that work in this case is

00:05:50.400 --> 00:05:51.650
any physical or mental activity

00:05:51.660 --> 00:05:52.470
of people.

00:05:52.950 --> 00:05:55.230
The earth is natural resources,

00:05:55.370 --> 00:05:57.390
minerals, water, forests, air,

00:05:57.510 --> 00:05:58.610
subsoil.

00:05:59.150 --> 00:06:00.910
Capital is, first of all, the accumulated

00:06:01.030 --> 00:06:04.590
stock of production factors,

00:06:04.600 --> 00:06:07.930
such as machinery, equipment,

00:06:08.110 --> 00:06:10.310
raw materials, materials.

00:06:11.390 --> 00:06:13.510
In this case, special attention should

00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:16.530
be paid to such a factor of

00:06:16.540 --> 00:06:18.030
production as technology.

00:06:18.040 --> 00:06:20.490
It is often considered as a component

00:06:20.500 --> 00:06:22.750
factor of capital production.

00:06:24.230 --> 00:06:27.670
Depending on the presence or endowment

00:06:27.680 --> 00:06:28.890
of factors of production,

00:06:28.900 --> 00:06:32.090
countries develop their specialization,

00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:35.150
organize production

00:06:35.160 --> 00:06:37.710
activities in their economic

00:06:37.720 --> 00:06:39.710
territories.

00:06:40.770 --> 00:06:42.650
Please look at the slide.

00:06:42.730 --> 00:06:44.850
By the origin of the factor

00:06:44.860 --> 00:06:46.350
of production could still be divided

00:06:46.360 --> 00:06:49.130
into the main and developed.

00:06:49.150 --> 00:06:51.390
These are the most natural

00:06:51.400 --> 00:06:53.970
factors developed and acquired.

00:06:54.710 --> 00:06:57.330
This division of factors has allowed

00:06:57.340 --> 00:06:59.810
a number of economists to develop

00:06:59.820 --> 00:07:00.990
the concept of international

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:03.210
competitiveness of nations,

00:07:04.210 --> 00:07:06.830
which proves that the presence

00:07:06.840 --> 00:07:09.450
of not only natural, but also

00:07:09.460 --> 00:07:11.370
the development of acquired

00:07:11.380 --> 00:07:14.410
factors leads to a faster development

00:07:14.420 --> 00:07:16.450
of the national economy.

00:07:17.110 --> 00:07:18.550
Let’s say Japan.

00:07:18.670 --> 00:07:20.850
It does not have a large set of

00:07:20.860 --> 00:07:22.430
basic natural factors, but is

00:07:22.850 --> 00:07:25.730
the leading country in international

00:07:25.740 --> 00:07:27.190
economic relations precisely

00:07:27.200 --> 00:07:29.510
because of the fact that it acquires

00:07:29.570 --> 00:07:32.290
and develops other factors

00:07:32.300 --> 00:07:34.830
of production around the world.

00:07:35.270 --> 00:07:37.170
According to the degree of specialization, the

00:07:37.180 --> 00:07:39.710
factors of production are divided into general specific factors.

00:07:40.210 --> 00:07:44.390
Common factors are used in any

00:07:44.400 --> 00:07:45.890
field of production

00:07:45.900 --> 00:07:47.550
and are assumed to have

00:07:47.560 --> 00:07:49.150
a fairly high mobility.

00:07:49.470 --> 00:07:50.930
Such factors of production could

00:07:50.940 --> 00:07:52.930
be attributed, for example, to

00:07:53.070 --> 00:07:54.630
laborers, who in any sphere

00:07:54.640 --> 00:07:56.870
of the economy engage in the

00:07:56.880 --> 00:07:59.170
same type of activity.

00:08:00.010 --> 00:08:02.110
Specific factors are less

00:08:02.120 --> 00:08:03.990
mobile, and often not mobile

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:05.670
at all, because they involve some

00:08:05.680 --> 00:08:08.810
special knowledge, special

00:08:08.820 --> 00:08:11.850
methods of economic activity.

00:08:12.190 --> 00:08:13.730
In the international economy, this

00:08:13.740 --> 00:08:15.510
division into general specific factors

00:08:15.520 --> 00:08:17.670
is due to the fact that the income

00:08:19.400 --> 00:08:21.450
of the owners of specific

00:08:21.460 --> 00:08:24.810
and general factors is different.

00:08:25.150 --> 00:08:26.630
If, for example, export-oriented

00:08:26.640 --> 00:08:28.890
sectors of the economy are developing,

00:08:28.900 --> 00:08:31.870
and in these sectors of the

00:08:31.880 --> 00:08:34.570
economy people are beginning to

00:08:34.580 --> 00:08:36.350
earn higher incomes, then,

00:08:36.360 --> 00:08:37.570
of course, the owners of

00:08:37.580 --> 00:08:39.670
specific factors, namely, for example,

00:08:39.680 --> 00:08:42.130
those very oil wells, will

00:08:42.140 --> 00:08:44.110
receive much greater incomes

00:08:44.120 --> 00:08:46.270
than the owners of common factors,

00:08:46.280 --> 00:08:48.810
namely engineers, namely, who

00:08:49.070 --> 00:08:50.810
do not possess any special

00:08:50.820 --> 00:08:52.970
qualification, and the same

00:08:52.980 --> 00:08:55.110
cleaners or programmers, which

00:08:55.120 --> 00:08:56.490
can be used in completely different

00:08:56.500 --> 00:09:00.530
fields of economic activity.

00:09:00.540 --> 00:09:03.390
Thus, the development of these groups

00:09:03.400 --> 00:09:05.710
of factors leads to the development

00:09:05.720 --> 00:09:07.590
of international division of labour,

00:09:07.730 --> 00:09:09.450
that is, a stable concentration

00:09:09.460 --> 00:09:11.190
of production of certain types

00:09:11.200 --> 00:09:14.990
of products in certain countries.

00:09:15.450 --> 00:09:16.890
The international division of labour

00:09:16.900 --> 00:09:19.650
presupposes the existence of its second

00:09:19.660 --> 00:09:22.870
half of the development of the international

00:09:22.880 --> 00:09:24.150
cooperative of production, but

00:09:24.160 --> 00:09:25.870
the international cooperative of

00:09:25.880 --> 00:09:27.450
production does not necessarily

00:09:27.460 --> 00:09:29.210
develop as a result of the development

00:09:29.220 --> 00:09:31.330
of the international division of labour.

00:09:31.430 --> 00:09:32.710
What does it have to do with?

00:09:33.450 --> 00:09:35.650
Suppose a less developed country,

00:09:35.660 --> 00:09:38.650
and it specializes in producing

00:09:38.660 --> 00:09:43.030
and even harvesting local

00:09:43.040 --> 00:09:44.650
fruits.

00:09:45.070 --> 00:09:47.710
Then, in principle, cooperation

00:09:47.720 --> 00:09:49.210
in fruit production,

00:09:49.220 --> 00:09:51.010
in general, is not needed.

00:09:51.050 --> 00:09:52.530
It is engaged in this production

00:09:52.540 --> 00:09:54.270
for its own consumption, and it

00:09:54.280 --> 00:09:55.510
is unlikely that these fruits

00:09:55.520 --> 00:09:57.690
can be exported at all.

00:09:58.290 --> 00:09:59.670
The process of cooperation

00:09:59.680 --> 00:10:01.290
still implies a high level of

00:10:01.300 --> 00:10:03.250
development of industrial production

00:10:03.260 --> 00:10:05.550
and begins to develop

00:10:05.560 --> 00:10:07.250
only when as a result of this

00:10:07.260 --> 00:10:09.610
cooperation the companies

00:10:09.620 --> 00:10:13.250
acquire some technological advantages.

00:10:13.510 --> 00:10:15.410
An example of such international

00:10:15.420 --> 00:10:19.190
cooperation is, suppose, the development

00:10:19.670 --> 00:10:24.290
of the finished

00:10:24.300 --> 00:10:26.670
clothing industry.

00:10:27.310 --> 00:10:28.990
Look, our domestic manufacturers

00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:31.510
no longer produce in our factories

00:10:31.520 --> 00:10:33.590
and factory, do not sew clothes

00:10:33.600 --> 00:10:34.570
in Russia.

00:10:34.970 --> 00:10:37.270
The technology of the model is being

00:10:37.280 --> 00:10:39.270
developed in Russia, production

00:10:39.280 --> 00:10:40.930
is organized in China as a cheaper

00:10:40.940 --> 00:10:43.010
option, but it is already

00:10:43.020 --> 00:10:44.770
spread, is being implemented

00:10:44.780 --> 00:10:46.210
again in Russia.

00:10:47.070 --> 00:10:49.310
Thus, international cooperation,

00:10:49.320 --> 00:10:50.870
I repeat, helps to save

00:10:51.230 --> 00:10:54.430
the very limited resources

00:10:54.440 --> 00:10:55.870
that are in society

00:10:55.880 --> 00:10:58.630
and to organize production

00:10:58.640 --> 00:11:00.090
effectively.

00:11:02.580 --> 00:11:06.100
If we pay attention to the scheme of the

00:11:06.110 --> 00:11:07.820
relationship between the types of division

00:11:07.830 --> 00:11:12.520
of labor, this scheme reflects the processes

00:11:12.530 --> 00:11:15.120
of development of the international

00:11:15.130 --> 00:11:16.020
division of labor.

00:11:16.180 --> 00:11:18.100
Initially, international division

00:11:18.110 --> 00:11:19.620
of labor developed as a national

00:11:19.630 --> 00:11:21.340
or regional division of labor,

00:11:21.350 --> 00:11:23.800
and over time firms began to

00:11:23.810 --> 00:11:25.500
specialize in the production

00:11:25.510 --> 00:11:27.920
of goods for export, and thus

00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:29.640
formed an international

00:11:29.650 --> 00:11:31.300
division of labor.

00:11:31.500 --> 00:11:33.420
What is the characteristic of the modern

00:11:33.430 --> 00:11:35.520
international division of labor?

00:11:36.320 --> 00:11:39.940
It is presented in the world in such

00:11:39.950 --> 00:11:42.640
forms as general, private, individual.

00:11:42.860 --> 00:11:45.500
What is meant here?

00:11:45.620 --> 00:11:47.640
On the one hand, the international

00:11:47.650 --> 00:11:49.260
division of labor can be common in

00:11:49.270 --> 00:11:51.360
large spheres of production, private

00:11:51.840 --> 00:11:53.960
- specialization in industries

00:11:53.970 --> 00:11:56.200
and sub-branches, and

00:11:56.210 --> 00:11:57.800
single - internal.

00:11:58.060 --> 00:12:02.540
Special attention is paid to the

00:12:02.550 --> 00:12:04.000
development of single internal

00:12:04.010 --> 00:12:05.420
division of labor, because international

00:12:05.430 --> 00:12:06.880
and transnational corporations

00:12:06.890 --> 00:12:09.980
organize the production

00:12:09.990 --> 00:12:13.200
process so that the entire production

00:12:13.210 --> 00:12:15.380
cycle is not organized in one

00:12:15.390 --> 00:12:17.940
country, but distributed in

00:12:17.950 --> 00:12:19.900
a number of countries depending

00:12:19.910 --> 00:12:22.020
on where the factors of

00:12:22.030 --> 00:12:25.520
production are cheaper.

00:12:26.780 --> 00:12:28.400
And thus the modern international

00:12:28.410 --> 00:12:30.400
division of labour at the level

00:12:30.410 --> 00:12:31.880
of the individual can

00:12:31.890 --> 00:12:34.060
be presented in such forms as in

00:12:34.070 --> 00:12:36.060
detail and operational.

00:12:36.070 --> 00:12:38.400
Imagine that technology is being developed

00:12:38.410 --> 00:12:40.380
to produce the same finished clothes

00:12:40.390 --> 00:12:42.200
in the United States, and

00:12:42.210 --> 00:12:44.500
in neighboring countries, border areas,

00:12:44.510 --> 00:12:47.240
for example, clothing is being

00:12:47.250 --> 00:12:49.420
uncovered, and in another country,

00:12:49.430 --> 00:12:51.960
the sewing of sleeves and pockets

00:12:51.970 --> 00:12:53.840
or buttons can be made.

00:12:55.660 --> 00:12:57.720
Thus, companies identify the

