00:26:02.960 --> 00:26:05.310
which represents the difference

00:26:05.320 --> 00:26:07.110
between exports and imports, or

00:26:07.120 --> 00:26:09.850
trade balance, as well as foreign

00:26:09.860 --> 00:26:12.330
trade turnover or the amount of

00:26:12.340 --> 00:26:14.810
exports and imports.

00:26:15.030 --> 00:26:16.670
Accordingly, if the country's

00:26:16.680 --> 00:26:18.570
exports exceed imports, then

00:26:18.580 --> 00:26:20.770
this is a positive trade balance.

00:26:20.780 --> 00:26:23.210
If, on the contrary, imports, which

00:26:23.220 --> 00:26:24.970
in general are less desirable

00:26:24.980 --> 00:26:27.530
than exports, then a negative

00:26:27.540 --> 00:26:29.830
trade balance in a given country.

00:26:30.070 --> 00:26:32.290
Ideally, all countries should

00:26:32.300 --> 00:26:34.150
try to balance their international

00:26:34.160 --> 00:26:36.810
trade and a

00:26:36.820 --> 00:26:40.090
balanced trade balance.

