03:06:38.840 --> 03:06:42.190
which implies that within corporate

03:06:43.190 --> 03:06:44.690
structures a firm transfers

03:06:44.700 --> 03:06:47.510
the right to use or its

03:06:47.520 --> 03:06:48.610
technologies, or

03:06:48.620 --> 03:06:50.410
transfers, suppose,

03:06:50.420 --> 03:06:52.010
the right to its trademark.

03:06:52.020 --> 03:06:53.290


03:06:53.300 --> 03:06:56.490
At the same time, this right, or

03:06:56.500 --> 03:06:57.870
rather not only the right, as

03:06:57.880 --> 03:06:59.550
many requirements to support the business,

03:06:59.560 --> 03:07:02.130
such methods of management

03:07:02.140 --> 03:07:04.110
and marketing, as developed

03:07:04.120 --> 03:07:05.590
in this firm.

03:07:05.970 --> 03:07:07.190
Therefore, in this regard, it can also

03:07:07.200 --> 03:07:08.490
be considered that franchising in

03:07:08.500 --> 03:07:12.210
a certain way, although formally not

03:07:12.220 --> 03:07:14.570
considered a direct transfer of

03:07:14.580 --> 03:07:16.070
technologies, but to a certain extent, however,

03:07:16.080 --> 03:07:17.750
franchising also contributes

03:07:17.760 --> 03:07:22.430
to the international transfer of technologies.

03:07:23.230 --> 03:07:25.870
Why do countries try to limit

03:07:25.880 --> 03:07:27.630
technology transfer?

03:07:28.430 --> 03:07:29.550
First of all, it is the desire

03:07:29.560 --> 03:07:31.270
to maintain technological leadership.

03:07:31.850 --> 03:07:36.290
Any monopoly has two sides.

03:07:36.370 --> 03:07:37.970
On the one hand, yes, this country

03:07:37.980 --> 03:07:38.810
will be a technological

03:07:38.820 --> 03:07:40.670
leader for some time, and on

03:07:40.680 --> 03:07:42.410
the other hand, it means that

03:07:42.420 --> 03:07:44.730
its technologies will be obsolete

03:07:44.740 --> 03:07:46.350
over time and it will need to support

03:07:46.360 --> 03:07:47.970
its technological leadership,

03:07:48.310 --> 03:07:50.370
invest a sufficiently high level

03:07:50.380 --> 03:07:53.230
of investment in these industries

03:07:53.240 --> 03:07:55.090
or in research and development.

03:07:55.170 --> 03:07:55.850
That means that it will

03:07:55.860 --> 03:07:57.850
need to maintain its technological leadership.

03:07:58.190 --> 03:07:59.610
And it is not necessary that at some

03:07:59.620 --> 03:08:04.230
stage in the process of some

03:08:04.240 --> 03:08:07.290
technical research this country, the

03:08:07.390 --> 03:08:08.870
technological leader, receives

03:08:08.880 --> 03:08:11.510
only one preference and dividends.

03:08:12.870 --> 03:08:14.230
The next reason for limiting the

03:08:14.240 --> 03:08:15.470
transfer of technology is

03:08:15.480 --> 03:08:17.330
the aggravation of national security.

03:08:18.010 --> 03:08:20.530
The state is trying to limit

03:08:20.540 --> 03:08:27.130
the spread of military technology.

03:08:27.140 --> 03:08:28.810
First of all, the technologies

03:08:28.820 --> 03:08:32.870
associated with the spread

03:08:32.880 --> 03:08:34.810
of various means of mass destruction.

03:08:35.470 --> 03:08:37.110
On the other hand, there are

03:08:37.120 --> 03:08:39.730
a lot of dual-use goods within

03:08:39.740 --> 03:08:42.430
the framework of national security.

03:08:42.870 --> 03:08:44.110
And then these technological

03:08:44.120 --> 03:08:45.910
developments of the state

03:08:45.920 --> 03:08:47.570
are interested, first of all, to

03:08:47.750 --> 03:08:49.670
develop their economies and

03:08:49.680 --> 03:08:53.230
transfer from the military sector

03:08:53.240 --> 03:08:55.570
to the civil sector within their economy.

03:08:56.290 --> 03:08:58.590
The next reason is the terms of

03:08:58.600 --> 03:09:00.210
international agreements.

03:09:00.220 --> 03:09:03.350
I have already talked about the COCOM

03:09:03.360 --> 03:09:06.630
agreement between NATO member countries,

03:09:06.970 --> 03:09:08.290
which regulates the transfer

03:09:08.300 --> 03:09:11.650
of military technologies

03:09:11.660 --> 03:09:12.870
and dual-use technologies.

03:09:12.970 --> 03:09:16.670
Certainly, countries that have their

03:09:16.680 --> 03:09:17.870
own national laws

03:09:17.880 --> 03:09:19.770
restricting the transfer of their

03:09:19.780 --> 03:09:24.470
technologies to the international

03:09:24.480 --> 03:09:25.790
sphere.

03:09:26.010 --> 03:09:28.330
They are very closely following this moment.

03:09:28.610 --> 03:09:30.430
In particular, for example, the United

03:09:30.440 --> 03:09:33.910
States, when trying to prove the

03:09:33.920 --> 03:09:36.430
illegality of any firm in any country,

03:09:36.440 --> 03:09:39.970
the transfer of goods, the

03:09:39.980 --> 03:09:41.470
sale of goods, some products to

03:09:41.480 --> 03:09:43.550
some third country, prove that it

03:09:43.690 --> 03:09:44.610
was in the development of

03:09:44.620 --> 03:09:46.810
its products that American

03:09:46.820 --> 03:09:48.630
technologies were involved.

03:09:48.730 --> 03:09:50.270
And often the percentage of this participation

03:09:50.280 --> 03:09:52.350
can reach 10 -15 percent.

03:09:52.570 --> 03:09:55.090
That is, this is a small component,

03:09:55.210 --> 03:09:58.090
but the United States justifies

03:09:58.100 --> 03:09:59.810
the introduction of either

03:09:59.820 --> 03:10:01.050
economic sanctions or bans

03:10:01.060 --> 03:10:02.750
of some kind, for these firms or

03:10:02.760 --> 03:10:04.250
for the entire economy in general,

03:10:04.260 --> 03:10:06.990
which has allowed such a spread

03:10:07.000 --> 03:10:10.830
of technology to those countries

03:10:10.840 --> 03:10:13.290
that, in the opinion of

03:10:13.300 --> 03:10:15.610
the United States, are

03:10:15.620 --> 03:10:17.410
politically unreliable.

03:10:19.420 --> 03:10:21.580
There are two mechanisms for regulating

03:10:21.590 --> 03:10:22.680
international technology

03:10:22.690 --> 03:10:23.700
transfer.

03:10:23.720 --> 03:10:25.460
Direct regulation is.

03:10:25.480 --> 03:10:27.020
Of course, these are bodies of export

03:10:27.030 --> 03:10:28.580
control, border, customs

03:10:28.620 --> 03:10:30.480
control and indirect control through

03:10:30.490 --> 03:10:35.020
the issuance of trade mark patents

03:10:35.030 --> 03:10:38.300
by the state, licenses for know-

03:10:38.310 --> 03:10:40.560
how, rendering of engineering

03:10:40.570 --> 03:10:44.420
services.

03:10:45.560 --> 03:10:48.580
Thus, in modern developed economies

03:10:48.590 --> 03:10:52.860
are trying to create an adequate

03:10:52.870 --> 03:10:57.880
mechanism for regulating the international

03:10:58.500 --> 03:11:01.340
transfer of technology, so that all

03:11:02.200 --> 03:11:06.180
the interests and contradictions

03:11:06.190 --> 03:11:08.600
that are associated with the international

03:11:08.610 --> 03:11:10.540
spread of technology, in the

03:11:10.550 --> 03:11:13.300
end, were resolved and did not

03:11:13.310 --> 03:11:16.160
inhibit economic growth and

03:11:16.170 --> 03:11:17.320
did not inhibit the

03:11:17.330 --> 03:11:19.640
spread of technical progress.

03:11:27.220 --> 03:11:28.880
The next topic we will discuss

03:11:28.890 --> 03:11:30.000
is the state regulation

03:11:30.010 --> 03:11:31.440
of foreign trade

03:11:31.450 --> 03:11:33.340
relations.

03:11:34.520 --> 03:11:37.160
First of all, let us pay attention

03:11:37.170 --> 03:11:40.360
to what are the objects

03:11:40.370 --> 03:11:42.040
of foreign trade regulation.

03:11:42.320 --> 03:11:44.620
In the narrow sense of the word,

03:11:44.630 --> 03:11:46.800
these are the flow of goods, exports,

03:11:46.980 --> 03:11:51.880
imports, undoubtedly the structure of

03:11:51.890 --> 03:11:54.660
exports and imports, the issues

03:11:54.670 --> 03:11:57.300
of trade balance of payments.

03:11:57.460 --> 03:11:59.940
However, in the broad sense of the

03:11:59.950 --> 03:12:03.160
word foreign trade relations concern

03:12:03.170 --> 03:12:06.120
financial relations, since for the sale

03:12:06.130 --> 03:12:08.240
of goods on export and import it is

03:12:08.250 --> 03:12:12.220
necessary to carry out some things are

03:12:12.230 --> 03:12:17.560
also the subject of our consideration,

03:12:17.570 --> 03:12:19.820
the balance of payments.

03:12:22.020 --> 03:12:24.020
Given that foreign economic agents

03:12:24.030 --> 03:12:26.680
pay taxes, the state budget, economic

03:12:27.060 --> 03:12:30.140
growth is also related to the

03:12:30.150 --> 03:12:32.760
development of foreign

03:12:32.770 --> 03:12:34.580
trade relations and is

03:12:34.590 --> 03:12:37.380
the object of foreign trade regulation.

03:12:38.660 --> 03:12:41.580
We must note that domestic

03:12:41.590 --> 03:12:43.080
and foreign

03:12:43.090 --> 03:12:44.880
policy are closely

03:12:44.890 --> 03:12:47.480
interrelated.

03:12:47.920 --> 03:12:50.540
Look at the slide.

03:12:51.160 --> 03:12:53.600
Fiscal policy itself can

03:12:53.610 --> 03:12:58.620
act as a factor of foreign

03:12:58.630 --> 03:13:00.120
trade regulation.

03:13:00.500 --> 03:13:02.180
If we raise domestic taxes,

03:13:02.190 --> 03:13:04.340
domestic goods start to

03:13:04.350 --> 03:13:06.260
cost more, and therefore

03:13:06.270 --> 03:13:11.560
they become foreign

03:13:13.120 --> 03:13:14.880
counterparties.

03:13:15.200 --> 03:13:17.820
Accordingly, a well-thought-out

03:13:17.830 --> 03:13:20.120
fiscal policy can replace measures

03:13:20.130 --> 03:13:22.300
of open protectionism

03:13:22.310 --> 03:13:24.920
when the state introduces quotas,

03:13:24.930 --> 03:13:28.480
tariffs and some other

03:13:28.490 --> 03:13:29.600
restrictions.

03:13:30.500 --> 03:13:33.800
Protectionism is

03:13:33.810 --> 03:13:36.520
taxation itself.

03:13:36.530 --> 03:13:40.560
And so-it is such a tariff policy

03:13:40.570 --> 03:13:43.260
involves fiscal goals, that is, supplementing

03:13:43.270 --> 03:13:45.220
the budget.

03:13:46.520 --> 03:13:47.780
On this basis, some developing

03:13:47.790 --> 03:13:50.520
countries have a policy of

03:13:50.530 --> 03:13:52.220
fairly tough protectionism

03:13:52.230 --> 03:13:54.900
precisely because they do not

03:13:54.910 --> 03:13:56.820
have other sources of budget

03:13:56.830 --> 03:13:59.720
refueling, or they are very limited.

03:14:00.920 --> 03:14:02.280
The next option is monetary

03:14:02.290 --> 03:14:03.780
policy.

03:14:04.040 --> 03:14:06.160
It can also be a substitute for

03:14:06.170 --> 03:14:08.600
open protectionism.

03:14:08.820 --> 03:14:10.840
Because monetary policy regulates

03:14:10.850 --> 03:14:13.820
the monetary mass in the

03:14:13.830 --> 03:14:14.700
economy.

03:14:15.940 --> 03:14:18.820
As you know, a rapidly growing

03:14:18.830 --> 03:14:21.040
money mass can cause inflation.

03:14:21.840 --> 03:14:23.720
This in turn will lead to a decrease

03:14:23.730 --> 03:14:25.320
in the exchange rate.

03:14:26.820 --> 03:14:29.000
It would seem that such a terrible

03:14:29.010 --> 03:14:31.820
internal situation as inflation and,

03:14:31.830 --> 03:14:33.880
in general, a decline in

03:14:33.890 --> 03:14:35.100
purchasing power, such as

03:14:35.110 --> 03:14:36.640
the ruble, will negatively

03:14:36.650 --> 03:14:38.400
affect consumers.

03:14:38.420 --> 03:14:40.380
But on the other hand, from the

03:14:40.390 --> 03:14:42.560
point of view of exports, such a

03:14:42.570 --> 03:14:44.720
credit-monetary policy is even preferable.

03:14:44.780 --> 03:14:45.160
Why is?

03:14:45.240 --> 03:14:48.440
Because the fall of the exchange

03:14:48.450 --> 03:14:50.440
rate will stimulate a relative

03:14:50.450 --> 03:14:52.680
depreciation of exports, and,

03:14:53.020 --> 03:14:55.060
accordingly, it will replace

03:14:55.070 --> 03:14:56.360
measures of open protectionism

03:14:56.370 --> 03:14:58.460
and support exports.

03:14:59.120 --> 03:15:01.020
Subjects of foreign trade regulation

03:15:01.030 --> 03:15:02.820
from the point of view of

03:15:02.830 --> 03:15:05.800
economists are the state, supra-

03:15:06.260 --> 03:15:09.380
state institutions and various

03:15:09.390 --> 03:15:11.580
international structures.

03:15:12.280 --> 03:15:14.420
From the point of view of law, the

03:15:14.430 --> 03:15:16.800
only subject of foreign trade relations

03:15:16.810 --> 03:15:18.440
is only the state, because

03:15:18.620 --> 03:15:22.940
all generally agreed international

03:15:22.950 --> 03:15:26.180
acts are ultimately rectified

03:15:26.190 --> 03:15:30.360
by the national based on this

03:15:30.370 --> 03:15:32.160
law, I repeat again, I

03:15:32.170 --> 03:15:34.080
assume that the only subject

03:15:34.090 --> 03:15:35.360
of foreign trade

03:15:35.370 --> 03:15:38.080
relations is the state.

03:15:38.380 --> 03:15:41.420
An example of this is Russia’

03:15:41.430 --> 03:15:43.480
s accession to the WTO.

03:15:43.640 --> 03:15:45.620
Before we become a final WTO

03:15:45.630 --> 03:15:49.760
member, Russia signs a lot of

03:15:49.770 --> 03:15:52.320
agreements with almost all

03:15:52.330 --> 03:15:56.540
150 WTO member countries on a

03:15:56.550 --> 03:15:58.660
bilateral basis and

03:15:58.670 --> 03:16:04.980
ratifies these agreements

03:16:04.990 --> 03:16:07.020
at the national state level.

03:16:08.980 --> 03:16:11.880
Foreign trade policy is a special

03:16:11.890 --> 03:16:15.840
area of economic relations and problems.

03:16:16.000 --> 03:16:18.200
The foreign trade policy is

03:16:18.210 --> 03:16:19.520
quite complex.

03:16:19.740 --> 03:16:21.200
The main problem is that we need

03:16:21.760 --> 03:16:23.240
to break out such an economic

03:16:23.250 --> 03:16:24.940
policy that would satisfy different

03:16:24.950 --> 03:16:27.020
groups, layers of the population.

