03:16:28.160 --> 03:16:29.460
And here comes the question

03:16:29.470 --> 03:16:30.800
of economic efficiency

03:16:30.810 --> 03:16:32.220
and social justice.

03:16:32.880 --> 03:16:35.500
On the one hand, market, market relations,

03:16:35.510 --> 03:16:37.620
competition contribute

03:16:37.630 --> 03:16:40.540
to the growth of economic efficiency.

03:16:40.960 --> 03:16:42.740
The foreign trade policy

03:16:42.750 --> 03:16:45.160
should be liberal.

03:16:47.700 --> 03:16:50.240
And less efficient producers, especially

03:16:50.340 --> 03:16:52.580
national ones, may eventually

03:16:52.590 --> 03:16:54.480
leave the world market,

03:16:54.490 --> 03:16:56.260
ruin themselves, because

03:16:56.840 --> 03:16:58.240
they organize production

03:16:58.250 --> 03:16:59.720
irrationally, use the

03:16:59.940 --> 03:17:02.940
factor of production irrationally.

03:17:03.460 --> 03:17:06.160
However, given the issue of

03:17:06.170 --> 03:17:08.600
social justice, such an effect from

03:17:08.610 --> 03:17:10.440
foreign trade policy would probably

03:17:10.450 --> 03:17:11.760
be negative for the development

03:17:11.770 --> 03:17:13.120
of the country.

03:17:13.400 --> 03:17:15.740
The second issue, the social

03:17:15.750 --> 03:17:16.980
justice issue, is therefore

03:17:17.940 --> 03:17:18.940
important.

03:17:19.380 --> 03:17:20.820
At least, when we consider for

03:17:20.830 --> 03:17:24.620
and against the introduction of

03:17:24.630 --> 03:17:27.560
tariffs, we will consider a number

03:17:27.570 --> 03:17:30.500
of aspects that push the state,

03:17:30.510 --> 03:17:32.460
the government, to include

03:17:33.040 --> 03:17:35.840
all the positions in foreign

03:17:35.850 --> 03:17:37.660
trade policy that support the social

03:17:37.670 --> 03:17:40.760
protection of citizens of

03:17:40.770 --> 03:17:42.660
the national economy.

03:17:44.280 --> 03:17:45.900
The foreign trade policy

03:17:45.910 --> 03:17:47.760
is a compromise.

03:17:47.800 --> 03:17:51.240
The compromise that economic agents

03:17:51.250 --> 03:17:53.680
have chosen for the given

03:17:53.690 --> 03:17:55.600
timeframe is a compromise

03:17:55.610 --> 03:17:57.140
between economic efficiency

03:17:57.150 --> 03:17:59.620
and social justice.

03:18:00.280 --> 03:18:02.720
The level of this compromise depends on the

03:18:02.730 --> 03:18:06.400
level of development of society.

03:18:07.380 --> 03:18:08.840
What are the barriers to the effectiveness

03:18:08.850 --> 03:18:10.200
of government regulation?

03:18:10.340 --> 03:18:11.960
After all, not everything goes smoothly,

03:18:12.040 --> 03:18:13.660
despite the fact that some legislative

03:18:13.670 --> 03:18:15.240
acts have been signed, some measures

03:18:15.250 --> 03:18:16.740
of foreign trade regulation

03:18:16.750 --> 03:18:18.300
have been developed.

03:18:18.820 --> 03:18:21.160
First of all, it is a rent-

03:18:21.170 --> 03:18:22.820
oriented behavior of politicians.

03:18:23.560 --> 03:18:25.320
Because foreign trade revenues

03:18:25.330 --> 03:18:26.500
are distributed unequally,

03:18:26.510 --> 03:18:29.220
as already mentioned in the previous

03:18:29.230 --> 03:18:32.780
lecture, owners of specific

03:18:32.790 --> 03:18:34.060
factors, unique factors,

03:18:34.120 --> 03:18:36.120
they usually get more income

03:18:36.130 --> 03:18:37.740
when world prices rise

03:18:37.750 --> 03:18:40.200
from foreign trade, and

03:18:40.210 --> 03:18:41.840
owners of neutral factors

03:18:41.850 --> 03:18:44.800
have less income.

03:18:44.840 --> 03:18:46.820
Moreover, all those who are involved

03:18:46.830 --> 03:18:48.700
in imports and replacement industries

03:18:48.710 --> 03:18:50.680
when prices fall due to the development

03:18:50.690 --> 03:18:52.780
of international trade,

03:18:53.060 --> 03:18:55.320
are virtually uncompetitive.

03:18:55.380 --> 03:18:58.640
These owners are losing income.

03:18:58.760 --> 03:18:59.960
So, the rental-oriented behavior

03:18:59.970 --> 03:19:02.040
of politicians is related to the group

03:19:03.600 --> 03:19:06.900
in which these politicians belong.

03:19:07.740 --> 03:19:11.180
The most relevant example.

03:19:11.700 --> 03:19:14.980
Suppose politicians are linked to agricultural

03:19:14.990 --> 03:19:16.160
parties.

03:19:16.520 --> 03:19:18.960
Of course, it is import and

03:19:18.970 --> 03:19:22.480
replacement sector with its own problems.

03:19:22.680 --> 03:19:24.720
And, of course, representatives

03:19:24.730 --> 03:19:26.940
of the agricultural parties will advocate

03:19:26.950 --> 03:19:28.180
a tough protectionist policy,

03:19:28.190 --> 03:19:30.540
which we have, for example, in the

03:19:30.760 --> 03:19:32.620
European Union.

03:19:33.280 --> 03:19:35.300
On the other hand, those policies

03:19:35.460 --> 03:19:38.300
belonging to the group of

03:19:38.520 --> 03:19:40.900
exporting raw materials such

03:19:40.910 --> 03:19:42.900
as oil and gas, in the conditions

03:19:42.910 --> 03:19:45.920
of the current market conditions,

03:19:45.930 --> 03:19:47.300
when prices of these energy

03:19:47.310 --> 03:19:49.640
sources are constantly

03:19:49.650 --> 03:19:51.720
rising, will be interested in

03:19:51.960 --> 03:19:54.160
developing the liberalization

03:19:54.170 --> 03:19:56.060
of foreign trade

03:19:56.070 --> 03:19:57.600
relations and expanding

03:19:57.610 --> 03:19:59.300
foreign trade.

03:19:59.860 --> 03:20:01.980
And eventually, these and others

03:20:01.990 --> 03:20:04.100
will conduct, lobby their decisions

03:20:04.110 --> 03:20:05.480
in government structures

03:20:05.490 --> 03:20:07.500
in order to conduct one

03:20:07.510 --> 03:20:09.000
or another type of

03:20:09.010 --> 03:20:10.480
economic policy.

03:20:11.140 --> 03:20:13.400
Subjective reason is also a barrier

03:20:13.410 --> 03:20:14.520
to the effectiveness

03:20:14.530 --> 03:20:16.640
of state regulation.

03:20:17.300 --> 03:20:19.320
The subjective reason is related,

03:20:19.330 --> 03:20:20.940
in general, to the development,

03:20:20.950 --> 03:20:22.620
to the literacy of those

03:20:23.020 --> 03:20:25.920
politicians who make state decisions.

03:20:26.120 --> 03:20:28.520
It is assumed that, if,

03:20:28.530 --> 03:20:29.840
of course, they have a theoretical

03:20:29.850 --> 03:20:31.420
economic education, they will

03:20:31.430 --> 03:20:33.480
adequately deal with the

03:20:33.490 --> 03:20:34.440
problems of state

03:20:34.450 --> 03:20:35.840
regulation and international

03:20:35.850 --> 03:20:36.920
economy.

03:20:37.260 --> 03:20:38.760
But on the other hand, they may

03:20:38.770 --> 03:20:41.000
have their own subjective views

03:20:41.010 --> 03:20:43.040
on how economic policy should

03:20:43.050 --> 03:20:44.820
be conducted, and, accordingly,

03:20:44.830 --> 03:20:46.020
they may curb the

03:20:46.030 --> 03:20:47.060
effectiveness of government

03:20:47.070 --> 03:20:48.940
regulation.

03:20:49.220 --> 03:20:51.140
The next aspect is hardware

03:20:51.150 --> 03:20:53.200
distortion or policy change.

03:20:53.680 --> 03:20:56.340
This reason is related to the

03:20:56.350 --> 03:20:57.720
two previous ones.

03:20:58.300 --> 03:21:00.880
In principle, you can legislatively

03:21:00.890 --> 03:21:03.900
develop very good laws and try

03:21:03.910 --> 03:21:05.880
to implement them in real

03:21:05.890 --> 03:21:07.080
practice.

03:21:07.260 --> 03:21:09.580
So, the apparatus, that is, those

03:21:09.590 --> 03:21:11.660
officials who implement these economic

03:21:11.670 --> 03:21:16.340
laws in practice, they can distort the

03:21:16.740 --> 03:21:20.780
policy goals in connection with the

03:21:20.790 --> 03:21:22.700
fact that they have their own group

03:21:22.710 --> 03:21:25.720
and personal interests, and they will

03:21:25.730 --> 03:21:28.440
lobby the interests of those

03:21:28.450 --> 03:21:30.360
groups to which they belong.

03:21:30.540 --> 03:21:32.700
The next reason is the influence

03:21:32.710 --> 03:21:34.540
of outdated economic concepts.

03:21:35.020 --> 03:21:38.120
The example is the state regulation

03:21:38.130 --> 03:21:39.220
in Russia.

03:21:40.200 --> 03:21:43.200
In the early 1990s, liberalization

03:21:43.210 --> 03:21:44.380
was the main principle

03:21:44.390 --> 03:21:46.680
of foreign policy.

03:21:48.320 --> 03:21:51.900
As part of liberalization, the Russian

03:21:51.910 --> 03:21:53.420
government sought to increase export

03:21:53.430 --> 03:21:56.080
and import flows in order to saturate

03:21:56.090 --> 03:21:58.820
the Russian economy with deficit

03:21:58.830 --> 03:22:01.500
goods and to remove the

03:22:01.510 --> 03:22:03.720
problem of food deficit.

03:22:04.620 --> 03:22:09.240
But by the year 95 the situation had evolved

03:22:09.250 --> 03:22:13.000
so that such liberalism was

03:22:13.010 --> 03:22:14.200
contrary to the interests

03:22:14.210 --> 03:22:15.660
of national producers.

03:22:16.280 --> 03:22:20.380
And, accordingly, liberalization

03:22:25.650 --> 03:22:29.040
has become somehow conducted

03:22:29.050 --> 03:22:32.080
tougher foreign trade policy.

03:22:32.300 --> 03:22:34.020
Russia has been negotiating

03:22:34.380 --> 03:22:36.760
its accession to the WTO

03:22:36.770 --> 03:22:38.140
since the same year.

03:22:38.320 --> 03:22:39.660
Accordingly, within such strategic

03:22:39.670 --> 03:22:42.420
objectives, the ideas and

03:22:42.430 --> 03:22:45.960
policies of liberalization must

03:22:45.970 --> 03:22:47.180
be carried out again.

03:22:48.220 --> 03:22:49.780
Productionism is

03:22:49.790 --> 03:22:51.360
now an outdated economic

03:22:52.060 --> 03:22:55.000
concept for the 2000s.

03:22:55.010 --> 03:22:56.660


03:22:57.060 --> 03:22:58.540
Ultimately, as I said, the

03:22:58.550 --> 03:23:02.760
result of a compromise can

03:23:02.770 --> 03:23:06.200
be some sort of intermediate

03:23:06.210 --> 03:23:08.200
foreign trade policy that

03:23:08.210 --> 03:23:10.020
takes into account different

03:23:10.030 --> 03:23:12.200
interest groups.

03:23:12.680 --> 03:23:14.100
The degree of development of

03:23:14.110 --> 03:23:15.900
market relations is also another

03:23:15.910 --> 03:23:17.980
reason for decreasing the effectiveness

03:23:17.990 --> 03:23:20.560
of state regulation.

03:23:20.760 --> 03:23:22.660
As practice shows, developed

03:23:23.020 --> 03:23:26.320
countries with a developed

03:23:26.330 --> 03:23:29.200
legal system more consistently

03:23:29.210 --> 03:23:31.940
implement state regulation measures.

03:23:32.660 --> 03:23:36.260
At the same time, countries with a

03:23:36.270 --> 03:23:37.980
transitional economy, the so-

03:23:37.990 --> 03:23:39.580
called transformational economy or

03:23:39.590 --> 03:23:43.600
a catching economy, within the framework

03:23:43.610 --> 03:23:47.180
of the underdevelopment of

03:23:47.360 --> 03:23:50.820
the legal framework,

03:23:50.830 --> 03:23:53.200
of course, the development of state

03:23:54.320 --> 03:23:57.800
policy is in more difficult circumstances

03:23:57.810 --> 03:24:02.300
and, accordingly, the results

03:24:02.310 --> 03:24:04.700
of such state policy can

03:24:04.710 --> 03:24:06.000
be less effective.

03:24:06.000 --> 03:24:08.400
The next factor is the degree of

03:24:08.410 --> 03:24:09.660
openness of the economy.

03:24:09.740 --> 03:24:12.440
Strangely enough, all countries,

03:24:12.450 --> 03:24:14.620
at least 150 members of the WTO, are

03:24:14.860 --> 03:24:16.040
generally in favor of

03:24:16.050 --> 03:24:17.540
a consistent liberalization of

03:24:17.550 --> 03:24:19.140
foreign trade relations.

03:24:19.820 --> 03:24:21.840
But as practice shows, once countries

03:24:21.850 --> 03:24:23.240
become sufficiently strongly

03:24:23.250 --> 03:24:24.840
integrated into international

03:24:24.850 --> 03:24:26.020
economic relations, into

03:24:26.030 --> 03:24:27.280
the international division

03:24:27.290 --> 03:24:30.520
of labor, as soon as they develop

03:24:30.530 --> 03:24:32.420
an export-initiated sector,

03:24:32.430 --> 03:24:35.520
they become dependent on the

03:24:35.530 --> 03:24:38.420
problems of cataclysms

03:24:38.860 --> 03:24:41.940
that may arise in the world economy.

03:24:43.700 --> 03:24:46.980
Based on this, the effectiveness

03:24:46.990 --> 03:24:49.420
of state policy in these national

03:24:49.430 --> 03:24:51.440
economies will actually depend

03:24:51.450 --> 03:24:53.500
on the overall global

03:24:53.510 --> 03:24:56.940
economic situation.

03:24:57.120 --> 03:24:59.300
Autoritarian actions of the state

03:24:59.310 --> 03:25:00.900
are another problem.

03:25:00.910 --> 03:25:04.020
And here the most typical example is the

03:25:04.030 --> 03:25:06.260
example of a state order.

03:25:06.380 --> 03:25:07.900
That is, by distributing

03:25:09.470 --> 03:25:11.640
government orders, our representatives

03:25:11.650 --> 03:25:13.640
of the state power will

03:25:13.650 --> 03:25:16.980
support various industrial

03:25:16.990 --> 03:25:19.840
groups, various industry

03:25:19.850 --> 03:25:22.260
structures to a certain

03:25:22.270 --> 03:25:23.420
extent.

03:25:24.520 --> 03:25:27.000
And, accordingly, these actions

03:25:27.010 --> 03:25:28.720
of the government can be

03:25:28.730 --> 03:25:31.240
authoritarian in nature, because,

03:25:31.280 --> 03:25:33.560
again, they are carried

03:25:33.570 --> 03:25:36.680
out by certain officials, and

03:25:36.690 --> 03:25:37.980
there is both rent-

03:25:37.990 --> 03:25:39.760
oriented behavior and hardware

03:25:39.770 --> 03:25:40.920
distortions.

03:25:42.480 --> 03:25:44.740
An example of such authoritarian

03:25:44.750 --> 03:25:47.000
actions by the state, for example,

03:25:48.200 --> 03:25:49.780
are the effects of environmental

03:25:49.790 --> 03:25:51.460
pollution.

03:25:52.140 --> 03:25:57.460
In particular, as is known, our

03:25:57.470 --> 03:25:59.540
corporation Minatom will import

03:25:59.550 --> 03:26:01.580
industrial waste from nuclear

03:26:01.590 --> 03:26:03.460
power plants to the territory

03:26:03.470 --> 03:26:05.560
of Russia in terms

03:26:05.570 --> 03:26:07.500
of economic efficiency.

03:26:07.880 --> 03:26:09.140
This is, of course, a positive

03:26:09.150 --> 03:26:10.940
result, because there are investments

03:26:10.950 --> 03:26:12.660
in the development of nuclear energy

03:26:12.670 --> 03:26:18.820
as a fee for the transport of

03:26:18.830 --> 03:26:19.720
such waste.

03:26:19.740 --> 03:26:21.480
But on the other hand, in terms

03:26:21.490 --> 03:26:24.620
of general social, global problems,

03:26:24.630 --> 03:26:27.420
they are only worsening.

03:26:28.020 --> 03:26:29.840
The next factor in reducing

03:26:29.850 --> 03:26:31.040
the effectiveness of state

03:26:31.050 --> 03:26:32.560
regulation is the

03:26:32.570 --> 03:26:34.480
mutually exclusive areas

03:26:34.490 --> 03:26:36.100
of state policy.

03:26:37.140 --> 03:26:38.980
I have already said how the

03:26:38.990 --> 03:26:40.560
credit-monetary and budget-tax

03:26:40.570 --> 03:26:42.480
policy is linked with

03:26:42.490 --> 03:26:44.260
foreign trade policy.

03:26:44.400 --> 03:26:45.920
And, accordingly, the government

03:26:45.930 --> 03:26:50.480
can take measures related to budget

03:26:50.490 --> 03:26:51.600
regulation, the Central

03:26:51.780 --> 03:26:54.540
Bank, measures of credit and monetary

03:26:54.550 --> 03:26:57.620
policy that will clearly level

03:26:57.630 --> 03:26:59.780
those steps that have been taken

03:26:59.790 --> 03:27:02.480
in foreign trade policy.

03:27:03.300 --> 03:27:05.840
Well, in this case, the simplest

03:27:05.850 --> 03:27:08.700
example, if the Central Bank

03:27:08.710 --> 03:27:11.100
for some reason refuses to support

03:27:11.110 --> 03:27:14.760
the decline of the ruble in modern

03:27:14.770 --> 03:27:16.560
conditions, the ruble price begins

03:27:16.570 --> 03:27:18.540
to rise, and this, in turn,

03:27:18.550 --> 03:27:23.060
again makes the prices

03:27:23.070 --> 03:27:26.980
of our export goods rise

03:27:26.990 --> 03:27:30.260
and makes them less competitive.

03:27:30.440 --> 03:27:33.100
And then, in the conditions

03:27:33.110 --> 03:27:35.340
of such a disadvantage,

03:27:35.350 --> 03:27:37.280
the liberal foreign trade policy, it

03:27:37.290 --> 03:27:39.440
will, in essence, contradict such

03:27:39.450 --> 03:27:41.400
activities of the Central Bank and

03:27:41.410 --> 03:27:43.300
the effectiveness of liberalization

03:27:43.310 --> 03:27:45.760
of foreign trade relations

03:27:45.770 --> 03:27:48.100
will decrease.

03:27:50.640 --> 03:27:53.200
There are two main trends in the development

03:27:53.210 --> 03:27:55.060
of foreign trade policy.

03:27:55.180 --> 03:27:56.300
This is free trading.

03:27:56.740 --> 03:27:59.840
The modern term of free trading is the

03:27:59.850 --> 03:28:02.720
liberalization of foreign trade relations.

03:28:04.540 --> 03:28:05.940
Freehandling implies the removal

03:28:05.950 --> 03:28:08.220
of all foreign trade restrictions

03:28:08.230 --> 03:28:11.360
and the development of free competition.

03:28:12.100 --> 03:28:14.320
Of course, the option

03:28:14.330 --> 03:28:15.440
of free-trade or liberal policy

03:28:15.450 --> 03:28:18.880
in absolute, full execution

03:28:18.890 --> 03:28:20.240
is impossible.

03:28:20.380 --> 03:28:22.380
Each country has its own national

03:28:22.390 --> 03:28:23.900
interests.

03:28:23.920 --> 03:28:25.920
Again, there are those industries,

03:28:26.140 --> 03:28:28.400
groups that should be protected

03:28:28.410 --> 03:28:29.560
socially.

03:28:29.740 --> 03:28:31.840
Therefore, no country has an

03:28:31.850 --> 03:28:34.880
ideal free-trade policy.

03:28:36.240 --> 03:28:38.980
In economic theory, you once studied

03:28:38.990 --> 03:28:41.760
the variant of perfect competition.

03:28:42.060 --> 03:28:44.560
Perfect competition, like absolute

03:28:44.570 --> 03:28:46.480
liberalization, are some hypothetical

03:28:46.490 --> 03:28:48.280
ideal models of development

03:28:48.290 --> 03:28:51.120
of foreign trade relations.

03:28:51.680 --> 03:28:52.960
and protectionism.

03:28:52.970 --> 03:28:54.920
Protectionism is another extreme in the

03:28:54.930 --> 03:28:56.660
development of foreign trade policy.

03:28:57.160 --> 03:28:58.720
It protects the internal

03:28:58.730 --> 03:29:02.040
market from foreign competition.

03:29:03.520 --> 03:29:04.740
And the second half

03:29:04.750 --> 03:29:07.880
of protectionist policy is related to

03:29:07.890 --> 03:29:10.060
the development, stimulation of

03:29:10.070 --> 03:29:12.380
export industries and, accordingly,

03:29:12.390 --> 03:29:14.280
the activities of the state to

03:29:19.210 --> 03:29:22.120
provide aid, the development of

03:29:22.130 --> 03:29:26.680
export firms and the capture of

03:29:26.690 --> 03:29:28.960
some foreign trade markets.

03:29:30.200 --> 03:29:33.860
The history of foreign trade policy of the

03:29:33.870 --> 03:29:37.620
20th century is quite dynamic.

03:29:37.980 --> 03:29:40.660
And this story shows how, depending

03:29:41.240 --> 03:29:42.140
on the economic, domestic

03:29:42.150 --> 03:29:43.800
and foreign economic situation,

03:29:43.810 --> 03:29:45.900
governments of different countries

03:29:45.910 --> 03:29:48.360
are fluctuating in developing

03:29:48.980 --> 03:29:50.660
foreign trade policies

03:29:50.670 --> 03:29:52.340
from policies close to

03:29:52.350 --> 03:29:54.820
greater liberalization

03:29:54.830 --> 03:29:57.440
to policies that involve

03:29:57.450 --> 03:29:59.420
stronger protectionist

03:29:59.430 --> 03:30:01.060
protective measures.

03:30:01.480 --> 03:30:05.040
If you take the beginning of the 20th century,

03:30:05.050 --> 03:30:07.700
the 30s is the period of the Great Depression.

03:30:07.940 --> 03:30:10.040
The objective of foreign

03:30:10.050 --> 03:30:11.940
trade policy is to protect

03:30:11.950 --> 03:30:13.360
national producers.

03:30:14.000 --> 03:30:16.540
This is why foreign trade policy of

03:30:16.550 --> 03:30:18.160
this period can be called

