Protection of emerging national industries.

03:44:39.630 --> 03:44:42.070
This argument is usually given

03:44:42.080 --> 03:44:44.170
by developing countries.

03:44:44.250 --> 03:44:48.470
For them, export-oriented

03:44:48.480 --> 03:44:50.090
production is often

03:44:50.100 --> 03:44:53.670
the main form of receiving

03:44:53.680 --> 03:44:58.130
national income.

03:44:58.140 --> 03:45:01.610
And, of course, as these

03:45:01.620 --> 03:45:03.370
countries develop

03:45:03.380 --> 03:45:05.090
industry, they become industrialized,

03:45:06.820 --> 03:45:09.170
and for some period the short-

03:45:09.180 --> 03:45:15.790
term protection of these

03:45:15.800 --> 03:45:18.550
new emerging industries

03:45:18.560 --> 03:45:21.070
is very important to these

03:45:21.080 --> 03:45:21.810
countries.

03:45:22.270 --> 03:45:25.070
This is considered a normal form

03:45:25.080 --> 03:45:27.570
of protection against international

03:45:27.580 --> 03:45:30.250
competition.

03:45:31.250 --> 03:45:32.690
Let us now consider the instruments

03:45:32.700 --> 03:45:34.070
of state regulation of foreign

03:45:34.080 --> 03:45:35.210
trade.

03:45:35.330 --> 03:45:37.730
There are many of them and they can

03:45:37.740 --> 03:45:41.170
be classified according to different principles.

03:45:41.650 --> 03:45:46.530
In general, the whole group of measures

03:45:46.540 --> 03:45:47.810
to protect the national economy,

03:45:47.870 --> 03:45:50.650
protectionist measures are divided into

03:45:50.660 --> 03:45:52.430
two large groups - tariff and

03:45:52.440 --> 03:45:53.930
non-tariff barriers.

03:45:55.990 --> 03:45:58.190
If you take tariff barriers, they

03:45:58.200 --> 03:46:00.630
include first of all the two

03:46:00.640 --> 03:46:03.750
most unique or most developed forms

03:46:03.760 --> 03:46:05.890
- these are customs duties

03:46:05.900 --> 03:46:07.730
and tariff quotas, which

03:46:07.740 --> 03:46:09.470
we will talk about later.

03:46:09.480 --> 03:46:12.350
Non-tariff measures are

03:46:12.360 --> 03:46:14.150
quantitative restrictions.

03:46:14.550 --> 03:46:16.510
Such restrictions are not

03:46:16.520 --> 03:46:17.790
welcomed by the international

03:46:17.800 --> 03:46:19.490
community because they

03:46:19.500 --> 03:46:22.810
completely block trade flows.

03:46:25.510 --> 03:46:28.250
Hidden measures of protectionism are

03:46:28.260 --> 03:46:29.930
sufficiently developed in modern conditions,

03:46:29.940 --> 03:46:32.110
and developed countries are trying

03:46:32.120 --> 03:46:33.850
to resort to them, because they

03:46:34.070 --> 03:46:36.510
are difficult to take into account

03:46:36.520 --> 03:46:39.050
other countries - counterparties, it

03:46:39.060 --> 03:46:40.450
is difficult to make claims to national

03:46:40.460 --> 03:46:42.050
economies and their governments

03:46:42.060 --> 03:46:43.890
on the introduction of hidden measures.

03:46:44.570 --> 03:46:46.570
A special block of state

03:46:46.580 --> 03:46:48.250
regulation tools is financial

03:46:48.260 --> 03:46:50.170
measures of protectionism.

03:46:50.530 --> 03:46:51.930
The courts cover subsidies,

03:46:51.970 --> 03:46:54.830
loans and various types of sanctions,

03:46:54.840 --> 03:46:57.870
including these dumped.

03:46:58.030 --> 03:47:03.050
Macroeconomic measures can be classified

03:47:03.060 --> 03:47:05.790
as a separate group, and they can

03:47:05.800 --> 03:47:07.270
be classified as hidden protectionism

03:47:07.280 --> 03:47:08.630
measures.

03:47:08.870 --> 03:47:11.630
Macroeconomic policy is strongly

03:47:11.640 --> 03:47:13.930
interrelated with foreign economic

03:47:13.940 --> 03:47:16.350
policy, and therefore it is possible

03:47:16.360 --> 03:47:19.270
to replace some of the methods

03:47:19.280 --> 03:47:20.770
used within the framework of the

03:47:20.780 --> 03:47:23.270
tariff policy of the state with

03:47:23.430 --> 03:47:25.510
methods of credit-monetary

03:47:25.520 --> 03:47:28.150
or budget-tax policy.

03:47:29.030 --> 03:47:31.270
The last group is quantitative financial

03:47:31.280 --> 03:47:32.490
measures.

03:47:33.190 --> 03:47:36.210
This is a special group because it

03:47:36.220 --> 03:47:38.390
is related to economic sanctions.

03:47:38.690 --> 03:47:43.650
Economic sanctions are not considered

03:47:43.660 --> 03:47:45.570
to be a common measure

03:47:45.580 --> 03:47:47.010
of state regulation.

03:47:47.070 --> 03:47:51.210
Economic sanctions are introduced

03:47:51.220 --> 03:47:53.230
to solve political problems.

03:47:53.550 --> 03:47:57.550
Economic sanctions use methods

03:47:57.560 --> 03:48:00.050
that block export

03:48:00.060 --> 03:48:02.510
and import flows.

03:48:02.520 --> 03:48:04.550
Of course, they are also the subject

03:48:04.560 --> 03:48:06.730
of consideration of economic

03:48:06.740 --> 03:48:09.790
sciences and the consequences of

03:48:09.800 --> 03:48:11.210
economic sanctions.

03:48:11.550 --> 03:48:13.450
The methods of imposing sanctions

03:48:13.460 --> 03:48:18.890
are understood in the economic theory and

03:48:18.900 --> 03:48:19.930
in the theory of international

03:48:19.940 --> 03:48:21.230
economic relations.

03:48:24.640 --> 03:48:27.760
So, let’s go to the first group

03:48:29.550 --> 03:48:34.560
of protectionist measures – customs duties.

03:48:35.820 --> 03:48:39.440
Difference between the term duty and tariff.

03:48:40.600 --> 03:48:42.360
A duty is a certain tax

03:48:42.370 --> 03:48:43.960
that is levied when imported

03:48:43.970 --> 03:48:48.420
or exported goods are

03:48:48.430 --> 03:48:49.740
introduced.

03:48:50.840 --> 03:48:52.560
But since in relation to

03:48:52.570 --> 03:48:57.340
different groups of goods these

03:48:57.350 --> 03:48:59.100
duties are differentiated,

03:48:59.260 --> 03:49:01.140
vary, they are assembled

03:49:01.150 --> 03:49:03.840
in a table called the tariff.

03:49:04.180 --> 03:49:06.800
Similarly, a tariff, for example,

03:49:06.810 --> 03:49:08.940
wages, that is, it is a grid

03:49:08.950 --> 03:49:13.800
of different levels of wages

03:49:13.810 --> 03:49:16.020
for different types of activities.

03:49:16.180 --> 03:49:18.200
All customs duties are collected

03:49:18.210 --> 03:49:21.040
in a certain grid, which

03:49:21.050 --> 03:49:22.800
is called a tariff.

03:49:23.380 --> 03:49:25.520
This is why customs duties

03:49:25.530 --> 03:49:27.120
are tariff measures.

03:49:27.480 --> 03:49:29.340
What are the functions of customs duties?

03:49:29.400 --> 03:49:30.520
First of all, the fiscal.

03:49:31.100 --> 03:49:32.940
This is a means of distributing

03:49:32.950 --> 03:49:34.400
income.

03:49:34.920 --> 03:49:39.340
If fiscal goals are predominant,

03:49:39.350 --> 03:49:43.180
then such a tariff policy

03:49:43.190 --> 03:49:47.520
is not ideal.

03:49:47.920 --> 03:49:51.340
The state understands that the

03:49:51.350 --> 03:49:54.660
general development of the

03:49:54.670 --> 03:49:56.920
economy and international

03:49:56.930 --> 03:49:59.440
economic relations is a necessary

03:49:59.450 --> 03:50:01.740
component of modern

03:50:01.750 --> 03:50:04.120
economic development.

03:50:05.300 --> 03:50:06.780
Therefore, the fiscal goal

03:50:06.790 --> 03:50:09.360
is present, but for developed

03:50:09.370 --> 03:50:13.100
countries it is a secondary goal.

03:50:13.300 --> 03:50:16.020
But for transitional economies,

03:50:16.030 --> 03:50:18.100
which have recently experienced

03:50:18.110 --> 03:50:21.000
some financial problems, which

03:50:21.010 --> 03:50:23.160
have a trade deficit, which

03:50:23.170 --> 03:50:24.940
have a budget deficit, these

03:50:24.950 --> 03:50:28.880
countries, of course, use customs

03:50:29.080 --> 03:50:31.040
duties as a means of receiving

03:50:31.050 --> 03:50:33.820
tax payments and as a means

03:50:33.830 --> 03:50:38.180
of supplementing the budget.

03:50:39.360 --> 03:50:40.240
The next function,

03:50:40.260 --> 03:50:43.220
protectionist, in this case is

03:50:43.230 --> 03:50:44.840
assumed to help us protect

03:50:44.850 --> 03:50:47.080
certain industries from international

03:50:47.090 --> 03:50:48.440
competition and,

03:50:48.450 --> 03:50:50.700
accordingly, promote

03:50:50.710 --> 03:50:52.860
the development of

03:50:52.870 --> 03:50:55.160
certain industries.

03:50:55.380 --> 03:50:57.800
Ultimately, this type of protectionism

03:50:57.810 --> 03:51:00.000
helps to influence

03:51:00.010 --> 03:51:01.860
not the balance of payments.

03:51:01.870 --> 03:51:04.660
If we have a negative balance of payments

03:51:04.670 --> 03:51:06.680
and import flows too large and

03:51:06.690 --> 03:51:08.880
too pressure on domestic

03:51:08.890 --> 03:51:11.740
competition, on the state

03:51:11.750 --> 03:51:13.520
of the domestic national economy,,

03:51:13.530 --> 03:51:17.120
the maintenance of measures of

03:51:17.130 --> 03:51:19.040
protectionism to reduce imports

03:51:19.050 --> 03:51:20.880
in some certain period of

03:51:20.890 --> 03:51:25.380
time is quite acceptable.

03:51:26.000 --> 03:51:26.980
The next function,

03:51:27.020 --> 03:51:29.820
balancing, is assumed that exports

03:51:30.040 --> 03:51:32.820
and imports develop primarily

03:51:32.900 --> 03:51:35.160
from the discrepancy of supply

03:51:35.170 --> 03:51:37.460
and demand in the domestic market.

03:51:37.560 --> 03:51:40.240
If we have a deficit in the

03:51:40.250 --> 03:51:43.200
domestic market, then we must

03:51:43.520 --> 03:51:45.480
liberalize our foreign trade

03:51:45.490 --> 03:51:47.320
relations and expand

03:51:47.330 --> 03:51:48.800
the flow of imports.

03:51:49.100 --> 03:51:50.640
If, on the contrary, there is

03:51:50.650 --> 03:51:53.280
a situation of excess goods, then

03:51:53.290 --> 03:51:56.220
we must in no way promote the

03:51:56.230 --> 03:51:59.000
export of excess goods abroad.

03:52:00.140 --> 03:52:01.940
There are a number of key principles

03:52:01.950 --> 03:52:03.260
of tariff policy.

03:52:03.680 --> 03:52:06.060
First of all, this is the principle of tariff escalation.

03:52:06.560 --> 03:52:08.600
What does he mean?

03:52:09.060 --> 03:52:11.360
Of course, all countries,

03:52:11.370 --> 03:52:13.440
having limited resources and,

03:52:13.450 --> 03:52:15.080
above all, raw materials,

03:52:15.090 --> 03:52:18.280
are interested in driving

03:52:18.290 --> 03:52:19.540
raw materials on their

03:52:24.580 --> 03:52:26.520
territory, which suggests that

03:52:26.530 --> 03:52:29.740
for some raw materials

03:52:29.750 --> 03:52:32.940
tariffs are quite low or cancelled,

03:52:32.950 --> 03:52:34.800
depending on the

03:52:34.810 --> 03:52:36.020
economic situation that

03:52:36.030 --> 03:52:37.520
develops within the

03:52:37.530 --> 03:52:39.700
national economy.

03:52:40.440 --> 03:52:42.260
If we import finished products,

03:52:42.270 --> 03:52:44.180
the higher the degree of processing

03:52:44.190 --> 03:52:45.880
of this finished product, the higher

03:52:45.940 --> 03:52:47.980
the tariff barriers.

03:52:48.100 --> 03:52:50.180
In particular, for components,

03:52:50.190 --> 03:52:51.800
which are then used in national

03:52:51.810 --> 03:52:54.340
production to assemble finished

03:52:54.350 --> 03:52:56.540
products on the territory

03:52:56.550 --> 03:52:58.260
of the national economy, tariffs

03:52:58.580 --> 03:53:00.960
are usually lower than for finished

03:53:00.970 --> 03:53:02.100
products.

03:53:02.760 --> 03:53:04.100
The simplest example.

03:53:04.600 --> 03:53:06.200
The tariffs for components for computers

03:53:06.210 --> 03:53:09.340
are lower than the tariffs for importing

03:53:09.350 --> 03:53:12.360
ready-made computers from other

03:53:13.480 --> 03:53:16.070
countries.

03:53:17.110 --> 03:53:18.050
The optimal rate.

03:53:18.060 --> 03:53:19.070
What is this principle?

03:53:19.530 --> 03:53:20.890
This principle is more

03:53:20.900 --> 03:53:22.870
theoretical than practical.

03:53:23.810 --> 03:53:29.090
It was developed in the institutions

03:53:29.100 --> 03:53:32.330
of the European Union when they discussed

03:53:32.340 --> 03:53:34.870
the question of what tariffs should

03:53:34.880 --> 03:53:36.490
be, what should be the system of protectionist

03:53:36.500 --> 03:53:39.510
measures within the European Union.

03:53:40.110 --> 03:53:43.590
The optimal rate is the rate that

03:53:43.870 --> 03:53:46.390
does not maximize taxes in the choice.

03:53:46.470 --> 03:53:48.030
The optimal rate is not one

03:53:48.230 --> 03:53:51.110
that allows to perform the fiscal

03:53:51.120 --> 03:53:52.650
function of the tariff.

03:53:52.660 --> 03:53:54.750
The optimal tariff is one that does not deteriorate

03:53:54.760 --> 03:53:57.190
the situation of national consumers, does

03:53:57.200 --> 03:53:59.810
not deteriorate the indicators

03:53:59.820 --> 03:54:05.570
of economic growth of the country.

03:54:05.930 --> 03:54:07.950
To some extent, the idea of an optimal

03:54:07.960 --> 03:54:09.930
tariff is generally a theoretical

03:54:09.940 --> 03:54:11.970
idea, but nevertheless this

03:54:11.980 --> 03:54:15.110
idea was used in the

03:54:15.120 --> 03:54:16.610
development of a system of protectionist

03:54:16.620 --> 03:54:19.610
measures in Western Europe.

03:54:21.100 --> 03:54:23.160
What is the classification of customs duties?

03:54:23.760 --> 03:54:27.080
We can divide them into at

03:54:27.090 --> 03:54:28.420
least three groups.

03:54:28.740 --> 03:54:31.040
First of all, the way of interplay.

03:54:31.240 --> 03:54:32.760
Two large taxes.

03:54:32.840 --> 03:54:35.400
The name add value in this case is

03:54:35.410 --> 03:54:37.580
a tax, which is imposed based

03:54:37.590 --> 03:54:40.080
on the value of the goods, that

03:54:40.090 --> 03:54:43.520
is, a tax on the price of the goods.

03:54:43.530 --> 03:54:44.560
specifically.

03:54:44.880 --> 03:54:46.480
In this case, it is assumed that when

03:54:46.680 --> 03:54:50.480
collecting the tax it is imposed

03:54:50.490 --> 03:54:52.600
based on the physiological

03:54:52.610 --> 03:54:54.140
characteristics of the goods, its

03:54:54.150 --> 03:54:57.440
specifics, that is, on tons, on square

03:54:57.450 --> 03:55:01.520
meters, on liters, for example,

03:55:01.530 --> 03:55:03.600
the volume of the engine and

03:55:03.610 --> 03:55:04.820
so on.

03:55:04.830 --> 03:55:06.900
Combined duties are the duties

03:55:06.910 --> 03:55:08.460
that use both the first

03:55:08.470 --> 03:55:11.020
and second principle.

03:55:11.600 --> 03:55:17.100
When a interest tax is declared on

03:55:17.110 --> 03:55:20.560
the import of some goods and at the same

03:55:20.570 --> 03:55:23.240
time it is indicated that the total

03:55:23.250 --> 03:55:25.820
value of the tax collected must

03:55:25.830 --> 03:55:28.160
not exceed, for example, 5 euros

03:55:28.170 --> 03:55:30.160
per tonne.

03:55:30.940 --> 03:55:33.960
According to the object of the appendix,

03:55:33.970 --> 03:55:35.780
customs duties are divided into import,

03:55:35.860 --> 03:55:37.840
export and transit duties.

03:55:38.060 --> 03:55:40.040
As you can see, in this case, the flow

03:55:40.050 --> 03:55:43.120
is expected to be accounted for.

03:55:44.020 --> 03:55:47.000
Of course, in the world community,

03:55:47.010 --> 03:55:49.120
first of all customs duties

03:55:49.130 --> 03:55:52.520
on import flow are retained.

03:55:55.520 --> 03:56:00.320
The reasons for this method of introducing

03:56:00.330 --> 03:56:02.380
import duties have already been considered.

03:56:02.600 --> 03:56:04.980
This is the export flow.

03:56:05.200 --> 03:56:07.780
The developed countries are not

03:56:07.790 --> 03:56:10.260
trying to raise the price of their exports.

03:56:10.400 --> 03:56:12.580
Export taxes are not usually

03:56:12.590 --> 03:56:15.380
applied in developed countries.

03:56:15.440 --> 03:56:17.440
For example, under U.S. legislation, there

03:56:17.450 --> 03:56:21.060
are no tariff restrictions on U.S. exports.

03:56:21.960 --> 03:56:23.500
But on the other hand, if we take,

03:56:23.510 --> 03:56:26.140
let’s say, Russia’s example,

03:56:26.150 --> 03:56:27.440
we know that we have export

03:56:27.450 --> 03:56:31.800
duties on exports of oil and

03:56:31.810 --> 03:56:33.720
gas, that is, energy.

03:56:34.220 --> 03:56:36.840
The purpose of such export duties,

03:56:37.440 --> 03:56:39.340
of course, is to impose such duties

03:56:39.350 --> 03:56:40.900
only if the world market conditions

03:56:40.910 --> 03:56:42.680
are such that prices of these

03:56:42.690 --> 03:56:45.200
export goods are rising.

03:56:45.400 --> 03:56:47.480
And of course, the excess

03:56:47.490 --> 03:56:49.160
income that export firms

03:56:49.170 --> 03:56:52.260
receive from energy exports,

03:56:52.270 --> 03:56:54.740
they are redistributed

03:56:54.750 --> 03:56:56.360
to the budget in favor

03:56:56.370 --> 03:56:57.200
of the state.

03:56:57.820 --> 03:56:59.040
Therefore, the purpose of such

03:56:59.050 --> 03:57:01.720
export duties is a redistributive

03:57:01.730 --> 03:57:02.860
fiscal function.

03:57:03.740 --> 03:57:06.120
Furthermore, in general, our

03:57:06.130 --> 03:57:07.800
domestic consumers are also interested,

03:57:07.810 --> 03:57:09.600
especially in the summer, in the

03:57:09.610 --> 03:57:10.840
rail-to-business country in the

03:57:10.850 --> 03:57:13.020
consumption of energy.

03:57:13.030 --> 03:57:14.880
Accordingly, in order to in this period

03:57:14.890 --> 03:57:16.020
of time somehow contain the

03:57:16.030 --> 03:57:19.460
flow of these goods on export,

03:57:19.470 --> 03:57:21.300
given that domestic prices for

03:57:21.310 --> 03:57:23.120
energy sources are usually contained,

03:57:23.130 --> 03:57:24.700
and lower, less advantageous

03:57:24.780 --> 03:57:26.380
to the exporter.

03:57:26.500 --> 03:57:27.900
So, the introduction of export

03:57:27.910 --> 03:57:30.100
duties allows to regulate these flows

03:57:30.110 --> 03:57:32.780
and protect the national already

03:57:32.790 --> 03:57:36.280
consumer and the deficit, one

03:57:36.290 --> 03:57:38.360
can say, or very important products

03:57:38.370 --> 03:57:40.840
to reorient to the domestic

03:57:40.850 --> 03:57:41.880
market.

03:57:42.040 --> 03:57:44.040
Transit duties are usually

03:57:44.050 --> 03:57:46.580
levied for the movement of goods

03:57:46.590 --> 03:57:48.200
from one country to another through

03:57:48.210 --> 03:57:51.020
the economic territory of a country.

03:57:51.240 --> 03:57:52.980
Transit duties are usually excluded

03:57:52.990 --> 03:57:55.340
from the developed countries.

03:57:56.040 --> 03:57:57.460
But, despite this, developing

03:58:00.870 --> 03:58:02.580
countries, transit duties are

03:58:02.590 --> 03:58:04.860
a means of supplementing the budget.

03:58:06.860 --> 03:58:09.140
Belarus transit duties on the

03:58:09.150 --> 03:58:11.680
export of Russian gas, Ukraine

03:58:11.690 --> 03:58:13.300
and so on.

03:58:14.420 --> 03:58:16.000
Often, of course, there are big

03:58:16.010 --> 03:58:17.620
disputes over transit duties, but in

03:58:17.700 --> 03:58:20.860
this national economy they replenish

03:58:20.870 --> 03:58:22.360
their budget at the expense of

03:58:22.370 --> 03:58:23.340
transit duties.

03:58:23.350 --> 03:58:25.640
According to the nature of the impact, the

03:58:25.650 --> 03:58:27.020
duties are divided into

03:58:27.120 --> 03:58:29.880
seasonal, compensatory, anti-dumping.

03:58:29.960 --> 03:58:32.780
Seasonal duties are usually imposed

03:58:33.160 --> 03:58:35.480
on goods according to supply

03:58:35.490 --> 03:58:37.060
and demand during a certain

