sanctions.

04:16:31.640 --> 04:16:33.380
I have said that economic sanctions

04:16:33.390 --> 04:16:36.720
are a form of continuation

04:16:36.730 --> 04:16:39.700
of political relations.

04:16:40.700 --> 04:16:43.000
The ultimate case of modern

04:16:43.010 --> 04:16:45.480
political relations is military

04:16:45.490 --> 04:16:46.620
action.

04:16:47.120 --> 04:16:49.940
Before the introduction of military

04:16:49.950 --> 04:16:52.020
action as part of economic threat,

04:16:52.030 --> 04:16:53.360
some countries impose

04:16:53.370 --> 04:16:54.960
economic sanctions.

04:16:55.300 --> 04:16:58.580
These sanctions have the greatest

04:16:58.590 --> 04:17:01.020
effect and effectiveness if they are

04:17:01.030 --> 04:17:02.780
imposed on all international communities

04:17:02.790 --> 04:17:05.240
within the framework of UN agreements,

04:17:05.420 --> 04:17:08.280
not on individual countries.

04:17:08.420 --> 04:17:10.260
However, many countries resort

04:17:10.270 --> 04:17:12.120
to economic sanctions as a preventive

04:17:12.130 --> 04:17:14.660
measure to address

04:17:14.670 --> 04:17:16.800
political problems.

04:17:17.680 --> 04:17:19.580
In this case, the leader

04:17:19.590 --> 04:17:21.500
in the introduction of sanctions

04:17:21.780 --> 04:17:22.860
is the United States, but

04:17:22.870 --> 04:17:26.560
Russia in the last 10 years

04:17:26.570 --> 04:17:30.580
often resort to the measure

04:17:30.590 --> 04:17:32.500
of economic sanctions.

04:17:34.740 --> 04:17:35.740
If you classify economic

04:17:35.750 --> 04:17:38.160
sanctions, they can be divided

04:17:38.170 --> 04:17:39.680
into trade embargo, point sanctions

04:17:39.780 --> 04:17:42.320
and financial sanctions.

04:17:42.720 --> 04:17:44.200
In principle, the introduction of

04:17:44.210 --> 04:17:46.140
a trade embargo implies that

04:17:46.150 --> 04:17:47.800
export and import flows to this country

04:17:47.810 --> 04:17:49.660
are blocked, with the exception

04:17:49.670 --> 04:17:52.480
of humanitarian flows within the

04:17:52.490 --> 04:17:54.820
framework of humanitarian

04:17:55.200 --> 04:17:58.600
aid, medicines, food products.

04:17:58.680 --> 04:18:01.780
Such a trade embargo has negative

04:18:01.790 --> 04:18:03.300
socio-economic consequences,

04:18:03.310 --> 04:18:05.140
so far as it is not likely

04:18:05.540 --> 04:18:07.620
that the wealthy class

04:18:07.630 --> 04:18:09.620
or those political leaders against

04:18:09.630 --> 04:18:11.680
whose policies these

04:18:11.690 --> 04:18:13.760
sanctions were directed

04:18:13.770 --> 04:18:14.540
suffer.

04:18:15.800 --> 04:18:18.680
The third party mostly affected

04:18:18.690 --> 04:18:20.420
by the introduction of the trade

04:18:20.430 --> 04:18:23.700
embargo is the ordinary population

04:18:23.710 --> 04:18:25.340
of the country.

04:18:25.460 --> 04:18:26.960
And often the introduction of a

04:18:26.970 --> 04:18:30.060
trade embargo has a negative effect.

04:18:30.500 --> 04:18:32.940
In particular, suppose the

04:18:33.060 --> 04:18:36.760
introduction of a ban on exports

04:18:36.770 --> 04:18:40.720
– imports of diamonds from the regions

04:18:40.730 --> 04:18:45.120
of South Africa, which was

04:18:45.130 --> 04:18:48.460
organized and directed against those

04:18:48.470 --> 04:18:51.340
militant groups that at this time

04:18:51.350 --> 04:18:54.360
developed military relations there.

04:18:56.760 --> 04:18:59.100
The consequences of these sanctions

04:18:59.110 --> 04:19:00.780
had a negative effect in that,

04:19:00.860 --> 04:19:03.160
once the legal flow of diamond

04:19:03.170 --> 04:19:05.060
import exports were blocked,

04:19:05.070 --> 04:19:07.320
the illegal trade developed,

04:19:07.330 --> 04:19:09.540
and moreover, the prices

04:19:09.550 --> 04:19:12.260
of these diamonds rose.

04:19:12.320 --> 04:19:14.820
Thus, the profits from growth,

04:19:15.120 --> 04:19:17.080
the world price growth, received

04:19:17.090 --> 04:19:19.660
just those groups against which economic

04:19:19.670 --> 04:19:21.620
sanctions were directed in

04:19:21.630 --> 04:19:23.580
the form of a trade embargo.

04:19:23.940 --> 04:19:25.800
In modern conditions, point

04:19:25.810 --> 04:19:28.400
sanctions are preferred.

04:19:28.480 --> 04:19:28.740
Why is?

04:19:28.880 --> 04:19:30.060
Because, first, they are aimed

04:19:30.070 --> 04:19:31.840
at a separate group of goods, and

04:19:31.850 --> 04:19:35.640
a more developed form of point sanctions

04:19:35.650 --> 04:19:37.720
is the direction of these restrictions

04:19:37.730 --> 04:19:40.620
in general on the activities

04:19:40.630 --> 04:19:42.600
of individual lists, on their movement

04:19:42.610 --> 04:19:45.080
between countries, entry, exit.

04:19:46.860 --> 04:19:48.680
In this case, such precise sanctions

04:19:48.690 --> 04:19:50.620
are supported by financial sanctions,

04:19:50.630 --> 04:19:53.500
when the accounts of those representatives

04:19:53.510 --> 04:19:57.020
of groups and parties against

04:19:57.030 --> 04:19:59.400
whose policies and economic

04:19:59.410 --> 04:20:01.240
sanctions were directed

04:20:01.250 --> 04:20:03.180
are arrested.

