and currency convertibility on capital

04:41:13.960 --> 04:41:17.190
accounts, we need to apply

04:41:17.200 --> 04:41:19.270
to the balance of payments

04:41:19.280 --> 04:41:21.270
scheme.

04:41:21.990 --> 04:41:23.150
Let us look carefully.

04:41:23.970 --> 04:41:26.150
The balance of payments consists of two

04:41:26.160 --> 04:41:27.350
large accounts.

04:41:27.360 --> 04:41:29.610
Account of current operations.

04:41:29.710 --> 04:41:31.690
The first item in the current

04:41:31.700 --> 04:41:36.310
account counts exports and imports.

04:41:36.710 --> 04:41:38.730
The difference between exports and

04:41:38.740 --> 04:41:40.970
imports is defined as the country’s

04:41:40.980 --> 04:41:42.470
trade balance.

04:41:42.480 --> 04:41:44.590
If exports are greater than

04:41:44.600 --> 04:41:46.250
imports, the trade balance

04:41:46.260 --> 04:41:47.930
is positive.

04:41:48.190 --> 04:41:51.770
The second article of the balance

04:41:51.780 --> 04:41:53.710
of payments is income received

04:41:53.720 --> 04:41:56.630
abroad and income paid abroad.

04:41:56.870 --> 04:41:58.410
Income of owners of

04:41:58.420 --> 04:41:59.430
factors of production,

04:41:59.440 --> 04:42:01.370
i.e. payroll, interest, profits

04:42:01.380 --> 04:42:03.210
related to foreign economic

04:42:03.470 --> 04:42:05.070
activity, are included

04:42:05.080 --> 04:42:06.690
in the account of current

04:42:06.730 --> 04:42:09.690
operations.

04:42:10.110 --> 04:42:11.670
And the last component of the

04:42:11.680 --> 04:42:14.210
current transaction account

04:42:14.220 --> 04:42:16.070
is current private transfers

04:42:16.080 --> 04:42:17.550
that are received from abroad

04:42:17.560 --> 04:42:19.370
or paid abroad.

04:42:19.380 --> 04:42:22.590
In this case, such current private

04:42:22.600 --> 04:42:25.490
transfers are expected.

04:42:25.500 --> 04:42:28.470
These are various donations, this

04:42:28.650 --> 04:42:30.710
is help that is provided

04:42:30.720 --> 04:42:33.210
by private organizations, not the state.

04:42:33.830 --> 04:42:36.910
So, if we now sum up the indicators

04:42:36.920 --> 04:42:39.150
of the left and right column presented

04:42:39.250 --> 04:42:42.350
on our scheme and find the difference

04:42:42.360 --> 04:42:45.410
between them, the balance of

04:42:45.420 --> 04:42:47.970
the current account allows us

04:42:47.980 --> 04:42:50.690
to take into account mainly foreign

04:42:50.700 --> 04:42:53.450
trade flows and income flows

04:42:53.460 --> 04:42:55.350
of owners, the factors of production

04:42:55.360 --> 04:42:59.590
that are organized in international

04:42:59.600 --> 04:43:02.250
economic relations.

04:43:02.350 --> 04:43:04.770
The capital account or the capital transaction

04:43:04.780 --> 04:43:07.310
account, first of all, the first

04:43:07.320 --> 04:43:10.070
component of the capital account,

04:43:10.080 --> 04:43:12.710
is foreign investment and

04:43:12.720 --> 04:43:14.510
domestic investment, which we

04:43:14.520 --> 04:43:15.730
transfer abroad.

04:43:16.370 --> 04:43:19.190
Both investments can be

04:43:19.200 --> 04:43:21.630
portfolio and direct, but

04:43:21.640 --> 04:43:23.370
it does not matter.

04:43:23.410 --> 04:43:25.030
They can, of course, be divided into

04:43:25.040 --> 04:43:27.570
the account, but we have all these

04:43:27.580 --> 04:43:29.810
investment flows of financial presence

04:43:29.820 --> 04:43:31.770
in the first line in the capital

04:43:31.780 --> 04:43:32.670
account.

04:43:33.290 --> 04:43:34.650
The second line is the

04:43:34.660 --> 04:43:37.090
influx of state foreign transfers.

04:43:37.310 --> 04:43:39.550
Here, the state aid, the flows

04:43:39.560 --> 04:43:42.390
of financial aid, provided by

04:43:42.400 --> 04:43:43.430
the state structures,

04:43:43.440 --> 04:43:45.170
are reflected in the capital

04:43:45.390 --> 04:43:49.430
account, as an indicator

04:43:49.440 --> 04:43:50.710
of state foreign transfers,

04:43:50.720 --> 04:43:53.150
influx and outflow

04:43:53.160 --> 04:43:53.970
abroad.

04:43:55.110 --> 04:43:57.330
Accordingly, in addition to donations

04:43:57.340 --> 04:43:58.950
or such free financial assistance,

04:43:58.960 --> 04:44:01.730
such as transfers, another component

04:44:01.740 --> 04:44:04.190
of financial flows between

04:44:04.200 --> 04:44:06.390
countries are loans.

04:44:06.690 --> 04:44:08.410
And then the next line of the capital account

04:44:08.420 --> 04:44:11.290
is the influx of loans to the country and the

04:44:11.300 --> 04:44:13.830
outflow of loans from the country.

04:44:14.070 --> 04:44:16.330
The balance of the capital account balances

04:44:16.430 --> 04:44:19.750
the right column of the account and it is

04:44:19.760 --> 04:44:23.770
assumed that there is a certain interdependence

04:44:23.780 --> 04:44:25.370
between the balance of the trade

04:44:25.380 --> 04:44:27.530
balance and the balance of the

04:44:27.540 --> 04:44:28.990
capital account.

04:44:29.930 --> 04:44:31.990
The total balance of payments

04:44:32.000 --> 04:44:34.850
is calculated as the amount of the

04:44:34.860 --> 04:44:37.130
balance of trade and as the balance

04:44:37.140 --> 04:44:40.630
of the capital account.

04:44:46.520 --> 04:44:48.660
Note that in this case, both

04:44:48.670 --> 04:44:51.540
the trade balance, the current

04:44:51.550 --> 04:44:53.660
account and the capital

04:44:53.670 --> 04:44:56.300
account are quite interrelated.

04:44:56.620 --> 04:44:58.820
If the country develops

04:44:58.830 --> 04:45:00.680
international trade, exports are

04:45:00.690 --> 04:45:04.140
quite thunderstorming, then there

04:45:04.150 --> 04:45:07.300
is usually a positive trade balance

04:45:07.310 --> 04:45:09.580
and a positive balance of

04:45:09.590 --> 04:45:11.240
current operations.

04:45:11.250 --> 04:45:15.520
Then the state in the country,

04:45:15.530 --> 04:45:16.580
the economic agents

04:45:16.590 --> 04:45:18.740
accumulate excess capital

04:45:18.750 --> 04:45:19.940
assets.

04:45:20.060 --> 04:45:23.220
And then such a country usually gives

04:45:23.230 --> 04:45:26.260
to the court, carries out foreign

04:45:26.270 --> 04:45:29.020
transfers abroad, carries out international

04:45:29.030 --> 04:45:30.220
investments.

04:45:30.320 --> 04:45:32.020
The capital account is the balancing

04:45:32.030 --> 04:45:33.900
item of the current transaction

04:45:33.910 --> 04:45:36.580
account.

04:45:36.640 --> 04:45:39.080
And if we can have a positive balance on

04:45:39.090 --> 04:45:41.600
the current account, this means that there

04:45:41.610 --> 04:45:43.580
is an influx into the country for payments,

04:45:43.590 --> 04:45:45.420
for trade operations, then

04:45:45.430 --> 04:45:47.620
usually on the account of capital

04:45:47.630 --> 04:45:51.300
there is a outflow of investment abroad.

04:45:51.380 --> 04:45:53.160
The capital account will therefore

04:45:53.170 --> 04:45:54.980
have a negative value.

04:45:55.120 --> 04:45:57.100
Plus and minus in the general, so to speak,

04:45:57.240 --> 04:45:58.920
arithmetic composition in this

04:45:58.930 --> 04:46:00.640
case gives zero.

04:46:00.940 --> 04:46:02.500
That is, if the balance of payments

04:46:02.510 --> 04:46:05.760
is balanced, then it is in our case

04:46:05.770 --> 04:46:07.860
if the situation is that foreign trade

04:46:08.900 --> 04:46:10.580
is less developed, imports are

04:46:10.590 --> 04:46:12.960
large enough, and exporters are not

04:46:13.580 --> 04:46:15.220
so competitive in the international

04:46:15.230 --> 04:46:17.480
market, then the account of

04:46:17.490 --> 04:46:19.740
current transactions becomes negative.

04:46:19.880 --> 04:46:23.240
And to cover these external economic

04:46:23.250 --> 04:46:26.300
payments, the state and firms

04:46:26.310 --> 04:46:28.020
have to make loans.

04:46:28.900 --> 04:46:31.440
And then the account of capital, again,

04:46:31.450 --> 04:46:33.520
balances the negative account of current

04:46:33.530 --> 04:46:36.260
operations, and the indicator of

04:46:36.270 --> 04:46:37.900
the account of capital in our country

04:46:37.910 --> 04:46:39.640
becomes positive, there is a capital

04:46:39.650 --> 04:46:41.420
inflow of capital assets into

04:46:41.430 --> 04:46:42.540
the country.

04:46:42.600 --> 04:46:45.020
Thus, I will repeat again, the first

04:46:45.620 --> 04:46:46.800
and second half of the

04:46:46.810 --> 04:46:48.840
balance of payments are mutually

04:46:48.850 --> 04:46:50.620
balanced articles.

04:46:50.840 --> 04:46:53.680
If the situation has arisen that it

04:46:53.690 --> 04:46:55.900
is impossible for a country to

04:46:55.910 --> 04:46:59.960
fully cover the shortfall of the current

04:46:59.970 --> 04:47:02.900
account at the expense of loans

04:47:02.910 --> 04:47:04.340
from some other investment flow,

04:47:05.000 --> 04:47:05.640
how then?

04:47:05.660 --> 04:47:07.600
Then the reserve pounds are used.

04:47:07.960 --> 04:47:09.340
And then the currency reserve

04:47:09.350 --> 04:47:11.720
fund, which is connected with the

04:47:11.730 --> 04:47:14.540
reserve currency, performs the

04:47:14.550 --> 04:47:18.320
function of the source from which

04:47:18.330 --> 04:47:20.720
the state, the Central Bank,

04:47:20.880 --> 04:47:23.040
covers its external debts.

04:47:25.680 --> 04:47:28.300
So, based on this, based on the concepts

04:47:28.310 --> 04:47:31.760
of current transactions and trading

04:47:31.770 --> 04:47:34.280
and capital account, we can find

04:47:34.290 --> 04:47:36.000
out, distinguish, forgive me,

04:47:36.010 --> 04:47:37.480
conversibility on current transactions,

04:47:37.490 --> 04:47:39.740
that is, the absence of restrictions

04:47:39.750 --> 04:47:41.380
on payments and transactions

04:47:41.390 --> 04:47:42.840
on current international

04:47:42.850 --> 04:47:44.660
transactions.

04:47:45.160 --> 04:47:46.300
Accordingly, it can be hard

04:47:46.310 --> 04:47:47.360
and soft.

04:47:48.180 --> 04:47:50.560
If we have a fixed exchange rate

04:47:50.570 --> 04:47:52.720
with you, then the conversibility

04:47:52.730 --> 04:47:55.520
on current transactions is tough.

04:47:56.000 --> 04:48:00.400
If we have a floating exchange rate

04:48:00.410 --> 04:48:02.560
with a regulated floating, then

04:48:02.820 --> 04:48:04.260
the conversibility on current

04:48:04.270 --> 04:48:06.600
transactions is soft.

04:48:07.620 --> 04:48:09.840
First, when entering the International

04:48:09.850 --> 04:48:11.520
Monetary Fund, countries are

04:48:11.840 --> 04:48:14.120
obliged to introduce conversibility

04:48:14.130 --> 04:48:16.340
on current transactions for

04:48:16.350 --> 04:48:18.220
their currency in order to support

04:48:18.230 --> 04:48:19.820
the development of international

04:48:19.830 --> 04:48:21.680
trade relations.

04:48:26.630 --> 04:48:28.290
The factors affecting

04:48:28.300 --> 04:48:30.010
the convertibility of currency on current

04:48:30.020 --> 04:48:32.450
transactions are quite diverse.

04:48:33.010 --> 04:48:36.790
As I have said in previous lectures,

04:48:36.800 --> 04:48:39.890
domestic and external economic

04:48:39.900 --> 04:48:41.830
development definitely affects

04:48:41.840 --> 04:48:45.270
the convertibility

04:48:45.280 --> 04:48:48.610
of currency by current transactions.

04:48:48.770 --> 04:48:50.730
If we have a liberal trade system,

04:48:50.740 --> 04:48:53.590
respectively, the economic

04:48:54.290 --> 04:48:55.450
barriers that contain

04:48:55.460 --> 04:48:57.650
exports and imports are quite

04:48:57.660 --> 04:49:01.030
low, then the rapid development

04:49:01.040 --> 04:49:03.810
of exports and imports leads

04:49:04.370 --> 04:49:08.530
to the stabilization of the

04:49:08.540 --> 04:49:11.250
national economy and economic

04:49:11.260 --> 04:49:12.910
growth and, accordingly,

04:49:12.920 --> 04:49:14.290
to a positive trade and

04:49:14.300 --> 04:49:16.390
payment balance.

04:49:16.510 --> 04:49:18.030
There is an influx of foreign

04:49:18.040 --> 04:49:21.470
currency, of course, at the same

04:49:21.480 --> 04:49:22.910
time there is a growth in

04:49:22.920 --> 04:49:27.090
demand for domestic currency as we export.

04:49:27.100 --> 04:49:29.970
In this case, your goods can be

04:49:29.980 --> 04:49:33.390
paid just from the exchange

04:49:33.400 --> 04:49:35.030
of foreign currency for domestic

04:49:35.040 --> 04:49:36.170
currency.

04:49:36.390 --> 04:49:37.710
And most importantly, there is

04:49:37.720 --> 04:49:39.790
an internal demand in the economy,

04:49:39.800 --> 04:49:42.270
and domestic demand again

04:49:42.280 --> 04:49:45.090
turns into domestic demand

04:49:45.100 --> 04:49:51.450
and is stable and, of course,

04:49:51.460 --> 04:49:55.090
its convertibility

04:49:55.100 --> 04:49:58.370
by current operations grows.

04:50:03.690 --> 04:50:05.090
Capital conversibility implies

04:50:05.100 --> 04:50:08.190
no limitations on payment and

04:50:08.200 --> 04:50:09.690
transfer on the capital

04:50:09.700 --> 04:50:11.250
account, which we have

04:50:11.390 --> 04:50:13.070
considered earlier.

04:50:13.550 --> 04:50:15.290
This implies that the currency

04:50:15.300 --> 04:50:17.130
is convertible for such transactions

04:50:17.140 --> 04:50:19.350
as direct portfolio investments,

04:50:21.810 --> 04:50:23.670
loans, capital grants.

04:50:23.870 --> 04:50:24.930
The requirements of the International

04:50:24.940 --> 04:50:26.030
Monetary Fund do

04:50:26.040 --> 04:50:27.330
not apply to the convertibility

04:50:27.340 --> 04:50:29.390
of capital transactions.

04:50:29.450 --> 04:50:31.610
Moreover, depending on the financial

04:50:31.830 --> 04:50:33.170
economic situation in the domestic

04:50:33.180 --> 04:50:35.170
market of the country,

04:50:35.180 --> 04:50:37.130
one or another, even developed,

04:50:37.140 --> 04:50:39.270
country introduces a restriction

04:50:39.280 --> 04:50:41.350
on convertibility on capital

04:50:41.360 --> 04:50:42.630
transactions.

04:50:42.890 --> 04:50:44.530
And even despite, for example, the

04:50:45.130 --> 04:50:48.350
fact that the US dollar is a solid

04:50:48.360 --> 04:50:51.390
convertible stable currency, but

04:50:51.400 --> 04:50:53.790
in a certain period of time the

04:50:53.800 --> 04:50:56.130
US government introduced

04:50:56.140 --> 04:50:58.390
a limit on convertibility on capital

04:50:58.400 --> 04:50:59.630
transactions.

04:50:59.650 --> 04:51:02.270
This was in the 1970s when

04:51:02.280 --> 04:51:04.970
the global financial

04:51:04.980 --> 04:51:07.030
crisis occurred.

04:51:11.620 --> 04:51:12.880
What are the most typical

04:51:12.890 --> 04:51:15.300
capital account restrictions?

04:51:15.960 --> 04:51:18.920
First of all, this is the restriction

04:51:18.930 --> 04:51:21.260
of objects of foreign direct investment

04:51:21.270 --> 04:51:23.680
in individual industries.

04:51:23.840 --> 04:51:25.740
The state prohibits foreign economic

04:51:25.750 --> 04:51:27.420
agents from investing

04:51:27.430 --> 04:51:31.260
or buying shares of strategic

04:51:31.270 --> 04:51:34.840
enterprises.

04:51:34.900 --> 04:51:37.360
The ban on opening accounts

04:51:37.370 --> 04:51:38.840
in foreign currency in

04:51:38.850 --> 04:51:40.540
foreign banks.

04:51:41.760 --> 04:51:43.560
The following limitation is the requirement

04:51:43.570 --> 04:51:45.180
for compulsory return of profits

04:51:45.190 --> 04:51:47.000
by domestic companies

04:51:47.140 --> 04:51:48.600
investing abroad.

04:51:49.920 --> 04:51:51.660
This requirement usually arises when

04:51:52.100 --> 04:51:55.140
a country’s national exchange rate

04:51:55.150 --> 04:51:57.380
is experiencing difficulties.

04:51:58.000 --> 04:51:59.480
The requirements to transfer or sell

04:51:59.490 --> 04:52:01.960
foreign currency received abroad, such

04:52:01.970 --> 04:52:03.440
a requirement was introduced by

04:52:03.450 --> 04:52:06.640
us and has been in effect for a long time.

04:52:07.540 --> 04:52:09.180
It was introduced by the Central Bank.

04:52:09.720 --> 04:52:12.020
In these conditions, when

04:52:12.030 --> 04:52:13.500
a positive balance of trade

04:52:13.510 --> 04:52:16.000
and payment balance is the

04:52:16.010 --> 04:52:18.960
main positive feature for

04:52:18.970 --> 04:52:22.420
the Russian economy, this

04:52:22.460 --> 04:52:24.800
requirement is undoubtedly removed,

04:52:24.860 --> 04:52:26.940
as is the requirement for the

04:52:26.950 --> 04:52:29.040
obligatory return of profits

04:52:38.530 --> 04:52:40.240
by national companies

04:52:40.320 --> 04:52:42.340
investing in foreign

04:52:42.350 --> 04:52:43.680
securities.

04:52:44.880 --> 04:52:47.440
This restriction at the current stage

04:52:47.450 --> 04:52:50.240
of development of Russia has been

04:52:50.250 --> 04:52:51.940
lifted, and our residents can

04:52:51.950 --> 04:52:53.500
buy foreign securities.

04:52:53.600 --> 04:52:55.880
The restriction is the presentation

04:52:55.890 --> 04:52:58.900
of foreign credit and other.

04:52:59.980 --> 04:53:01.480
In general, the form of capital account

04:53:03.930 --> 04:53:04.420
restrictions is quite diverse.

04:53:06.220 --> 04:53:08.680
Depending on how quickly a country

04:53:08.690 --> 04:53:11.820
is moving towards the full

04:53:11.830 --> 04:53:13.220
convertibility of its currency,

04:53:13.230 --> 04:53:19.260
it removes certain restrictions.

04:53:19.600 --> 04:53:22.520
The general principle is that if we have

04:53:22.530 --> 04:53:25.100
limited convertibility on the account

04:53:25.110 --> 04:53:28.260
of capital, then we have no outflow

04:53:28.270 --> 04:53:29.320
of capital.

04:53:30.120 --> 04:53:32.340
Naturally, such a form of

04:53:32.350 --> 04:53:33.780
restriction will be used primarily

04:53:33.790 --> 04:53:35.680
by transitional economies or developing

04:53:35.690 --> 04:53:38.520
countries, or countries that

04:53:38.530 --> 04:53:40.460
experience problems in

04:53:40.470 --> 04:53:43.100
the national cyclical

04:53:43.110 --> 04:53:45.660
development of economies.

04:53:47.080 --> 04:53:48.680
Full convertibility just implies

04:53:48.690 --> 04:53:50.440
that we have no restrictions,

04:53:50.450 --> 04:53:52.660
no control on both the current

04:53:52.670 --> 04:53:54.880
account and the capital

04:53:54.890 --> 04:53:56.620
account.

04:54:00.840 --> 04:54:02.600
Russia is experiencing a difficult path to

04:54:02.610 --> 04:54:07.020
convertibility of the ruble.

04:54:07.400 --> 04:54:10.400
In Russia’s development programmes for the

04:54:10.410 --> 04:54:13.480
next three years, the Central Bank is

04:54:13.490 --> 04:54:19.640
confused about the goal of bringing

04:54:19.650 --> 04:54:22.160
Russia to full convertibility of the ruble.

04:54:22.240 --> 04:54:24.100
Therefore, the currency liberalization

04:54:24.110 --> 04:54:25.720
is progressively implemented.

04:54:25.820 --> 04:54:28.000
Other restrictions are removed.

04:54:28.600 --> 04:54:32.520
In particular, in this case, one of

04:54:32.530 --> 04:54:34.960
the options that push the recognition

04:54:34.970 --> 04:54:37.440
of the weight to the convertibility

04:54:37.450 --> 04:54:39.740
of the ruble is the law introduced

04:54:39.750 --> 04:54:42.020
by the Central Bank from January

04:54:42.030 --> 04:54:45.220
1, 2007, according to which

04:54:45.230 --> 04:54:47.640
our domestic exporters

04:54:47.650 --> 04:54:51.720
pay taxes to the budget in

04:54:51.730 --> 04:54:54.260
the domestic currency.

04:54:54.320 --> 04:54:56.560
Thus, the exchange of dollars, euros

04:54:56.570 --> 04:54:58.940
against the Russian ruble is stimulated

04:54:58.950 --> 04:55:00.900
and the demand for domestic currency

04:55:00.910 --> 04:55:03.700
is increasing, its stability is affirmed.

04:55:04.420 --> 04:55:07.340
Another measure that is being carried

04:55:07.350 --> 04:55:10.180
