and then adjust it, it can be there

05:23:33.290 --> 05:23:35.260
to conduct a policy of supporting

05:23:35.270 --> 05:23:38.260
this exchange rate,

05:23:38.270 --> 05:23:39.840
the mechanism of non-intervention

05:23:39.850 --> 05:23:42.440
of the state and independent

05:23:42.450 --> 05:23:44.540
floating of the exchange

05:23:44.550 --> 05:23:46.520
rate is included.

05:23:46.580 --> 05:23:49.560
In particular, in the 70s, at the time

05:23:49.570 --> 05:23:51.540
of the financial and currency

05:23:52.140 --> 05:23:55.060
crisis, European countries for 1-2

05:23:55.070 --> 05:23:57.020
months completely released their exchange

05:23:57.030 --> 05:23:58.500
rates to somehow orient

05:23:58.510 --> 05:24:01.300
themselves in the currency space.

05:24:07.760 --> 05:24:09.220
What are the modern ways to

05:24:09.230 --> 05:24:10.980
fix the exchange rate?

05:24:13.540 --> 05:24:15.100
The most common fixation on one currency,

05:24:15.110 --> 05:24:18.160
but nevertheless many countries

05:24:18.170 --> 05:24:20.220
fix the exchange rate at the cost

05:24:20.230 --> 05:24:22.200
of a basket of currencies.

05:24:22.600 --> 05:24:24.140
For example, modern Belarus fixes its

05:24:24.150 --> 05:24:26.560
exchange rate to the basket of solid

05:24:26.570 --> 05:24:28.260
currencies, the dollar and the euro, but

05:24:28.270 --> 05:24:31.340
also to the currency of neighbouring countries,

05:24:31.350 --> 05:24:33.660
that is, Poland, Lithuania, Latvia,

05:24:33.780 --> 05:24:34.860
Ukraine.

05:24:35.080 --> 05:24:37.200
Since September 1, 2000, the Russian

05:24:37.210 --> 05:24:38.980
ruble has been included in

05:24:38.990 --> 05:24:41.340
the fixation basket by the Central

05:24:41.350 --> 05:24:43.000
Bank of Belarus.

05:24:44.730 --> 05:24:47.570
Traditionally, when fixing the

05:24:47.580 --> 05:24:51.450
value of currency, fixing the

05:24:51.460 --> 05:24:53.030
exchange rates of the value of the

05:24:53.040 --> 05:24:57.950
currency basket, the most stable

05:24:57.960 --> 05:25:00.090
partners in international

05:25:00.100 --> 05:25:03.950
trade and currency-financial

05:25:03.960 --> 05:25:06.230
relations are used.

05:25:06.240 --> 05:25:10.670
In history, when the European

05:25:10.680 --> 05:25:14.290
Union was not yet a single currency,

05:25:14.300 --> 05:25:16.870
many developing countries, former

05:25:16.880 --> 05:25:19.830
colonies of European countries,

05:25:19.840 --> 05:25:23.990
just fixed their exchange rates

05:25:24.000 --> 05:25:28.370
to the former metropolis,

05:25:28.380 --> 05:25:30.450
for example, to the French

05:25:30.460 --> 05:25:33.590
franc or to the German mark.

05:25:34.990 --> 05:25:37.410
This trend hasined to a certain

05:25:37.420 --> 05:25:39.550
extent for them, as they now

05:25:39.560 --> 05:25:41.350
fix their exchange rate

05:25:41.360 --> 05:25:43.170
to the euro.

05:25:45.840 --> 05:25:47.780
A soft form of fixing the exchange

05:25:47.790 --> 05:25:50.140
rate is the currency corridor.

05:25:50.560 --> 05:25:52.240
This is also a variant of regulated

05:25:52.250 --> 05:25:55.340
floating, but it is assumed that the

05:25:55.350 --> 05:25:57.460
state the central bank announces

05:25:57.470 --> 05:25:59.980
in advance, at what intervals,

05:25:59.990 --> 05:26:02.180
within what limits the exchange

05:26:02.190 --> 05:26:04.260
rate will fluctuate.

05:26:04.270 --> 05:26:06.900
A fixed exchange rate is also subject

05:26:06.910 --> 05:26:11.340
to the possibility of some deviation.

05:26:11.820 --> 05:26:12.140
Why is?

05:26:12.260 --> 05:26:14.120
Because there is a currency

05:26:14.130 --> 05:26:16.520
market with free supply

05:26:16.530 --> 05:26:18.280
and demand, and the influence

05:26:18.360 --> 05:26:20.120
of supply demand can cause the

05:26:20.130 --> 05:26:22.720
market exchange rate to deviate

05:26:22.730 --> 05:26:24.660
from a fixed exchange

05:26:24.670 --> 05:26:25.720
rate.

05:26:26.020 --> 05:26:27.860
And so as not to affect

05:26:27.870 --> 05:26:30.420
the stability of the national

05:26:30.430 --> 05:26:32.920
currency, central banks at a

05:26:32.930 --> 05:26:34.540
fixed exchange rate allow deviations

05:26:34.550 --> 05:26:36.980
within the range of

05:26:36.990 --> 05:26:39.400
1.5 to 2.5%.

05:26:39.410 --> 05:26:42.420
Once the fluctuations reach

05:26:42.430 --> 05:26:46.900
the upper or lower limit of 1.

05:26:46.910 --> 05:26:49.680
5% the central bank intervenes

05:26:49.690 --> 05:26:52.240
and adjusts the exchange

05:26:52.250 --> 05:26:53.260
rate.

05:26:53.380 --> 05:26:55.460
If the central bank has not had

05:26:56.910 --> 05:26:59.480
enough funds to connotate, then

05:26:59.490 --> 05:27:01.780
the exchange rate is devalued,

05:27:01.790 --> 05:27:03.420
that is, it decreases.

05:27:03.620 --> 05:27:06.180
Or, on the contrary, if the trend

05:27:06.190 --> 05:27:08.180
of the world market is that the currency

05:27:08.190 --> 05:27:09.880
should be stronger, there is

05:27:10.020 --> 05:27:12.380
a revolution, as it was again in

05:27:12.390 --> 05:27:14.820
the 20th century with the Japanese

05:27:14.830 --> 05:27:16.900
yen, when they were unable

05:27:16.910 --> 05:27:18.560
to support a lower exchange

05:27:18.570 --> 05:27:20.900
rate with their central bank

05:27:20.910 --> 05:27:21.800
resources.

05:27:23.020 --> 05:27:25.100
So back to the currency corridor.

05:27:25.320 --> 05:27:27.420
The regulated floating within the

05:27:27.430 --> 05:27:29.720
currency corridor already implies

05:27:29.730 --> 05:27:34.580
fluctuations of more than 2 -3%.

05:27:34.590 --> 05:27:39.800
In particular, in Russia, before 1998

05:27:39.810 --> 05:27:41.820
for a number of years there was

05:27:41.830 --> 05:27:43.900
a currency corridor, so the width

05:27:43.910 --> 05:27:47.560
of the currency corridor was 15%.

05:27:47.570 --> 05:27:50.960
In 96-97 just before the currency crisis,

05:27:50.970 --> 05:27:52.320
it was slightly reduced to 13%,

05:27:52.330 --> 05:27:56.880
but in general it was not able to

05:27:56.890 --> 05:27:59.620
finally hold the fluctuations

05:27:59.630 --> 05:28:01.220
of the exchange rate.

05:28:08.220 --> 05:28:12.240
If we talk about the currency corridor

05:28:12.260 --> 05:28:15.660
used in the 70s, there was a rather

05:28:15.670 --> 05:28:17.460
interesting situation when the

05:28:17.470 --> 05:28:19.520
currency corridor was called generally

05:28:19.530 --> 05:28:21.660
"the snake in the tunnel", because the

05:28:21.670 --> 05:28:23.420
upper and lower bar of this tunnel were

05:28:23.430 --> 05:28:25.600
determined by European countries

05:28:25.610 --> 05:28:28.940
by the sum of the upper bar,

05:28:28.950 --> 05:28:30.420
that is, in this case it is the

05:28:30.430 --> 05:28:31.820
cheapest exchange rate, by the

05:28:31.830 --> 05:28:33.840
sum of the weakest currencies,

05:28:33.850 --> 05:28:35.620
and the lower bar, that is,

05:28:35.630 --> 05:28:37.400
a strong exchange rate when the

05:28:37.410 --> 05:28:39.060
currency and national rate

05:28:39.070 --> 05:28:40.580
fluctuate, by the group

05:28:40.590 --> 05:28:43.260
of the strongest currencies

05:28:43.270 --> 05:28:45.480
of the European Union.

05:28:46.380 --> 05:28:48.380
Again, this version of the currency corridor

05:28:48.390 --> 05:28:50.580
was able for the European Union to

05:28:50.590 --> 05:28:52.760
hold only a few months in that period

05:28:52.770 --> 05:28:54.520
of time, and accordingly the

05:28:54.530 --> 05:28:57.580
European Union monetary system came

05:28:57.590 --> 05:28:59.840
to the conclusion that it was necessary

05:28:59.850 --> 05:29:01.900
to simply release currency

05:29:01.910 --> 05:29:03.440
rates and maintain them at

05:29:03.450 --> 05:29:06.620
the expense of the intervention

05:29:06.630 --> 05:29:08.800
of the Central Bank without the

05:29:08.810 --> 05:29:11.140
announcement of the currency corridor.

05:29:13.320 --> 05:29:18.020
What is the current situation in the

05:29:18.030 --> 05:29:19.400
Russian currency system?

05:29:19.780 --> 05:29:23.600
In Russia, there is a floating

05:29:23.610 --> 05:29:25.980
exchange rate, but it is again

05:29:25.990 --> 05:29:27.320
regulated swimming.

05:29:27.900 --> 05:29:29.360
The currency corridor has already

05:29:29.580 --> 05:29:31.280
been canceled as the Russian ruble has

05:29:31.290 --> 05:29:33.680
become more stable and is subject to

05:29:33.690 --> 05:29:35.220
less fluctuations.

05:29:35.560 --> 05:29:37.560
The second reason for stabilization

05:29:37.570 --> 05:29:41.000
is the huge influx of oil dollars or

05:29:41.010 --> 05:29:48.420
euro oil currencies, which

05:29:48.430 --> 05:29:50.540
flows into the Russian financial territory

05:29:50.550 --> 05:29:52.980
in connection with the price

05:29:52.990 --> 05:29:54.920
of oil and energy growers.

05:29:56.700 --> 05:29:59.160
When the current exchange rate of

05:29:59.170 --> 05:30:03.280
the Russian ruble is determined in modern

05:30:03.290 --> 05:30:06.940
conditions, they do not use the quadrosystem,

05:30:06.950 --> 05:30:09.600
that is, the system I have

05:30:09.610 --> 05:30:10.960
already mentioned, when we

05:30:10.970 --> 05:30:12.440
have euro, dollars, yen, and pounds

05:30:12.450 --> 05:30:15.400
of sterling in our currency reserves,

05:30:15.680 --> 05:30:19.460
they use for current calculations

05:30:19.470 --> 05:30:21.180
a binary currency basket,

05:30:21.190 --> 05:30:23.320
that is, euros and dollars.

05:30:23.420 --> 05:30:27.520
60% of the calculations are in dollars,

05:30:27.530 --> 05:30:28.720
and accordingly, fluctuations

05:30:28.730 --> 05:30:30.300
